<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
    <FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="2">
      <Content>
        <Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Bold">Title card: </Text>
<Text Style="Underline+Bold">January</Text>
<Text Style="Bold"> </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">EXT. BENSONHURST, BROOKLYN, STREET - MORNING</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Walking briskly down a commercial block on a cold morning, ZEV STERN (early 20s), with black curly hair, is wearing khakis, a blazer, an overcoat, and worn white sneakers.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He arrives outside Cinema Four, an arthouse movie theater. The dirty bulbs and rusted marquee weathered by years of poor business still gives away hints of past grandeur. As he approaches the glass doors, he checks his pulse under his neck. He peers into the theater's lobby; keeping in theme with the eroded exterior, the lobby is shoddy, with worn red velvet carpet lining the floor and walls.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ALAN'S OFFICE - SHORTLY BEFORE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">ALAN (60s) the owner of Cinema Four, is at his desk, cigarette in hand, scribbling into an accounting notebook. He's a worn man, with features bloated from years of financial stress.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Behind Alan is a large spread of old photos and newspaper clippings from the theater's glory days.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sprawled across the small office, dejected after a long, grueling meeting is the theater's crew, who are all wearing the standard Cinema Four uniform: for the men, a brown suit with a white shirt and name tag with their position. For the women, a brown tweed skirt with long white socks and a white shirt.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew consists of:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">JIMMY (30s), the theater's manager. Short, glasses, receding hairline, with an underwhelming stature. He stands closest to Alan, with a clipboard and street-cart coffee.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">MARY (early 30s), the theater's curator. Bohemian and commanding, she's covered with tasteful poke and stick tattoos.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">CONNIE (early 20s), usher, a flower child who's floaty and a true sweetheart. Keeping her hair up with a bandana, she's the only one sitting on the floor, legs crossed. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">ROBERT (mid 20s), ticket seller, derives his look and demeanor from his heroes - Andrei Tarkovsky and Peter Bogdanovich. A filmmaker himself, with no credits, he wears a neck scarf and sunglasses. Strapped across his chest, ready for use at a moment's notice, is a vintage director's viewfinder.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">WARREN (mid 20s), usher, portly and jolly. He stands beside Robert, his partner in filmmaking endeavors. He is holding the book </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Notes on the Cinematographer</Text>
<Text Style=""> by Robert Bresson and a large soda from the concession stand. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">CHARLOTTE (mid - late 20s), the theater's projectionist. She stands away from the table, almost separated from the rest of the crew. She has an effortless sophistication and natural beauty.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After a sustained silence, Connie shouts, exasperated.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Why don't we just rope it off?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The idea hangs in the ether. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie, if you rope it off, then the second row </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">becomes</Text>
<Text Style=""> the first row.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie is unconvinced.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Our problem isn't the construct of the front row. We're talking about seat-to-screen </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">distance</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy throws his arms out in complaint.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(frustrated)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Distance</Text>
<Text Style=""> is a construct. It's only relative to your perspective of the third dimension.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(turning to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he is unresponsive)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(snapping)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How the hell is this a team meeting when half the room refuses to speak?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren, standing beside Robert, nudges him subtly. Behind his sunglasses, life flutters, Robert leans forward.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The devil's in the details, but so is salvation. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he takes hold of his viewfinder)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're far, but...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking into the viewfinder and zooming)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now you're close. Who's to say where you really are?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy takes his glasses off and grips his eyes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm going to stroke out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy, relax.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Relax?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he snatches a letter from Alan's desk)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"The Brooklyn Borough Small Claims Court has ruled in favor of the plaintiff. Cinema Four LLC must pay $1,607 dollars and 39 cents to the Levine family for injuries sustained during a fifteen hour screening of </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Berlin Alexanderplatz.</Text>
<Text Style="">"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(skimming)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"rampant negligence" ...  "past trauma" ... "the siege of Leningrad" ... </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(scanning for the important part)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Damages cover the purchase of nine AirFlow Max neck braces and $75 dollars per person in pain and suffering."</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert sighs deeply.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Mary)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wasn't this during </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Shoah</Text>
<Text Style="">?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It was a double feature.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How did nobody notice, for twenty five straight hours, nine... </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">litigious</Text>
<Text Style=""> individuals?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(glaring at Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte! You didn't think that was a touch strange? An empty theater and a packed first row?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quick retort)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They could've been nearsighted or just wanted an immersive experience.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">At least alert The General!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't even try to bring this down on me! Besides, The General thinks he's fighting for a hill in South Pacific. You run this place, own up!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Jimmy)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She's right.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You and The General are the only ones who have eyes in the screening room. That's all I'm saying.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So now I work the projection booth and security? Should someone print me a new badge? I do </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">my</Text>
<Text Style=""> job, and if you're going to parade him around as "security" - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(interrupting Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Stop. Connie, can you go find The General please? He should be here to defend himself against this ableist slander. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie stands and scurries out of the office. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Luckily, Charlotte can afford Ativan. Keep the crazy at bay, so she can have a solid lucidity about the world around her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie walks quickly through the lobby. Zev is where we last left him, peering through the glass entrance doors. When he sees her, he softly knocks in hopes of getting her attention. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie sees Zev and approaches the door. She takes a quick glance at her watch - 8:57am. She pulls a blind from above the door and walks away. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is startled and stuck staring at a "CLOSED" sign. He tries the door, which is locked. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan rests his cigarette in an ashtray. He sighs deeply and looks at his staff. The crew, including Jimmy, turn and wait for him to say something. Alan takes a moment, wiping his mouth with his hand in hesitation of delivering bad news.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know how much this hurts me... and - and I'm working on bringing someone in who's done this before and can bring us back to the golden days. I don't want be the boogeyman, but the lease is up at the end of the year and I have no idea if we'll be able to afford the new one. Definitely not by getting sued. Not to mention, we still have to replace poor Isaac.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(stopping to smoke)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Covering the neck braces comes out to $68.39 per head for the next six weeks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The room is silent.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What about pain and suffering?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jesus Christ, Mary, we're all suffering!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, no, he's right. You've all done more than enough for the Four, and you know how grateful I am.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Alan, kindly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We share in profit AND we share in the losses. When things pick back up, you'll be stuffing our envelopes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This place hasn't turned a profit in 15 years.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Is this going to push back our shoot dates?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sighing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No... I'll have to go to Brooklyn Mirage this weekend and sell some tranq. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(worried)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But, the lifetime ban!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It must be done.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(despondent)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll pay... I should've been watching.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't you dare - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie comes back into the room, followed by Zev, who has his hands zip-tied behind his back. THE GENERAL follows closely into the office after him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">THE GENERAL, the theater's janitor and security, is a middle aged man dressed in a commander's uniform studded with military accolades and carrying a broom. He comes off as mentally unsound, possibly schizophrenic, either way unaware of reality.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I caught him scoping out the perimeter. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sheepish)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh, so he sees a customer standing outside six minutes before we open and he's got the guy in shackles?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev, a whisper audible to all)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She's about as dry as a new nun's nest.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a silence as the group examines Zev. He is uncomfortable receiving their collective gaze. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm here for the concession stand job. Or Zaidenberg told my mother I should stop by... He said Alan would be expecting me.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan's eyes light up. He stands to greet Zev warmly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That would be me son. Come on in. Zaidenberg is a good man. Sold me a lemon once, but what's a lemon between friends?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(chuckling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan walks over and warmly greets with him an outstretched hand, which cannot be reciprocated by Zev who is still detained.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to The General)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Free this man.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The General begrudgingly cuts the zip-tie with an army knife.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(muttering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Big mistake. Big. Huge.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN &amp; CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in unison)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Pretty Woman!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren and Connie giggle.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ever work a cinema?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No. I used to work for my uncle's car dealership, but he recently went under -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He has experience with failing business, seems like a perfect fit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(clearing his throat)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Under investigation.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ah. Well, still. Dark stuff.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev nods and squeaks out shy smile.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ignoring Warren)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ever work with food?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A few summers ago, I was a delivery driver for Nathan's in Brighton.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're replacing </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Isaac</Text>
<Text Style=""> with a guy who drove around in a hot dog shaped truck? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I kind of agree with that.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the crew)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But we don't know when he's coming back or if he'll ever even walk again.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's Oscar Meyer, with the hot dog truck, not Nathan's. Nathan's is just a regular truck.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group looks at Zev for the truth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(gesturing to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's right, it's just a painted U-Haul.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary begrudgingly accepts this information. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Alan)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What do you figure this does for the payments?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan thinks for a moment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Probably gets you down to about 17, 18 bucks a person.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy takes this as a strong point for Zev's employment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to himself)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ooph, sweet cheddar... </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the group)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Uh... I feel like standard protocol? Majority rules?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan nods.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What's your name son?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">All in favor of Zev here to join us, say aye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(lukewarm)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(unenthusiastic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nay, for nepotism. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(doesn't care)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sweetly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(shaking Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aye, abstain.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And the "ayes" have it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(shaking Zev's hand)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Welcome to Cinema Four.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's a slow afternoon at Cinema Four and the foyer is deserted, save for Zev, who is at the helm of the concession stand for his first day on the job.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Last renovated in the 1970s, the theater has been in permanent decay through years of diminishing business and financial strain, which is reflected in the threadbare carpets and kitsch decor.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Bookending the foyer are a glass concession stand at one end and a velvet couch, a relic from the cinema’s opening in the 1930s, at the other; a circular lounge area spreads out halfway between them. Extending from the lobby is a hallway leading to the screening room with a staircase to the balcony and projection booth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert and Warren come as a pair behind the concession stand, not acknowledging Zev's existence, and pour themselves sodas from the fountain.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jerry was wrecked on set. I won't stand for that on my crew. He's a messy bastard and a filthy drunk.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's been sober for 25 years; I've never even seen him sip a cup of coffee. And he's the best technician in town.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Right, I forgot you're the perceptive one. You're a goddamn space cadet!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah so were The Beatles.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But you never saw their crew stumbling around turning up the amps to 11!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You just think he's a homophobe.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I caught him reading a John Ford biography. He thinks John Wayne made a great Genghis Khan for Chrissake!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So what? Maybe he has eye for those western cuties. Tell me you don't.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The searchers are basically genocidal reactionaries. How can he shoot our movie toting a 1950s vision of masculinity? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary comes into the theater with a large brown paper bag filled with lunches.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy exits Alan's office and walks towards Mary. Mary hands out subs to Warren, Jimmy, Robert, and Connie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Did you remember, no vinaigrette?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Warren)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Of course. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Connie)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie, sweetie, I texted you and  you never replied. They were all out of Soba and I knew you wouldn't eat cold cuts, so here's some French bread.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oui oui.  </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy takes a couple of bites and scurries over to Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sorry, pal, where were we?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Press the cup against the metal and the soda comes out. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN (O.S)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(from across the lobby)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey Mary, do you mind?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary walks behind the counter to join Zev. She picks up where Jimmy left off.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay... So, you've got your fountain, snacks, popcorn, pump, napkins, and straws. And we're cash only, but giving our fair share to the Uncle Sam is a pillar of what it means to work at Cinema Four. So, don't lose the receipts.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(serious)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Understood.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Also we have a strict No Outside Snacks and Beverages policy. Before each showing, we search a few patrons at random. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(low voice)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Between you and me, it's always the seniors, but we aren't ageists.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary opens a cabinet under the stand revealing an assortment of snacks in a basket labelled "contraband". </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After the show they can pick up whatever we confiscate, but they almost always forget. We put the good ones back up for sale.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev ruffles through the bin. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Two OLD GRANNIES walk into the theater. Mary glances at them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(chuckling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know, when I picked </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Salò</Text>
<Text Style="">, I never thought we'd pack the house with golden girls. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev gulps as he watches Mary walk to the ticket counter and meet the old grannies. He surveys the lobby. Connie and Warren stand by the velvet rope that separate the lobby from the screening rooms.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The two women approach Connie. GRANNY #1 has a tote bag with soda and candy. GRANNY #2 has a walker with an IV drip. They hand their tickets to Connie, Warren stands by.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Granny #1)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hi ladies, can I see some tickets?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Granny #1 has the tickets for the two of them. She hands them to Connie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GRANNY #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The theater sent me these, for my birthday.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well happy birthday! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking at the ticket, it has an "x" marked on it)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oop! Looks like I'm going have to conduct a snack search.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GRANNY #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you consent to be searched by this gentleman here? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GRANNY #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't you dare touch me with your thorns.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thorns ma'am?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GRANNY #2</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Horns, thorns! We don't want you hopped up looking for something sweet. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(gesturing to Connie)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She can do it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren shoots a glance to Connie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Actually ma'am, I... enjoy men. She... </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(gesturing to Connie)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">enjoys men </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">and</Text>
<Text Style=""> women. So technically, she'd be the thorny one.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The grannies are visibly confused. Connie sees the situation getting sticky and quickly shuts it down.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Never mind! Enjoy the movie ladies. And happy birthday!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The grannies walk past them into the screening room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - MINUTES LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev sees the rest of the crew gathered off to the side on the velvet couch eating their sandwiches together. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I just don't know what we're going to do.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We did fine, seven tickets for a Tuesday evening. What do you want, a full house?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Two of them were comped. Birthday tickets.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shit, Connie, we stopped the birthday tickets years ago. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev watches them chat, feeling alienated by himself at the stand. He looks down below the counter at a Ziplock bagged PB&amp;J.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He takes a bite of the sandwich and gingerly pours himself a soda, looking around to see if anyone notices, but the crew are all busy bantering inaudibly to one another.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The grannies are watching the movie. The granny with the IV drip removes the tube from her arm and puts it in her drink. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The lobby is calm.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev's elbows rest on the concession stand countertop; he's slowly adjusting to the slow rhythms of Cinema Four. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Within earshot, Robert and Warren are huddled around a payphone, sharing the receiver between them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello? Hi Mr. Galowitz thanks for joining the line - no we were just talking shop, we're ready when you are.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(listening)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Uh huh. Okay. Here's Robert.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren nudges Robert. Robert doesn't take the receiver.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Talk me up!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a touch frantic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert, Robert, he's a great guy, he's the next big thing, what else can you say?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(away from the receiver to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What else can I say?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert snatches the receiver.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello? Mr. Galowitz?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes, yes. Just to warn you - it's very literary - very expressive - a bit nebulous, so it can be hard to describe. It's about a kid who grew up in New Jersey. He's spent his entire life looking across the Hudson at the Manhattan skyline. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren pulls the phone in-between them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So close, yet so far.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Exactly. The only time his parents ever let him go into the city was on a school field trip, to the Met, in the late 90s. And that's the New York he fell in love with, the one from the 90s. And so he grows up, spending every day, every waking moment, fantasizing about the city. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Then he gets to be a little older, more independent, and he returns to the city.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On the bus. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On the bus, that's right. He gets there and he hates it. Nothing's right, it's full of chain restaurants; a neon shit version of Disneyland. He feels such deep sadness at its decline, so he sets out to document the end of the city, to capture those last gleaming images of authenticity.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And then it becomes like a documentary. It's an entirely new type of movie, not completely fiction, not completely documentary. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Warren)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I could've said it better myself. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in receiver)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's not even about characters, really. It's about motion, movement, sensation. Like </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Koyaanisqatsi.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert looks confused.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mr. Galowitz? It's Warren now.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(listening)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes, of course I know he doesn't have any credits. We discussed this - he's up and coming.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(putting the receiver to his chest)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He doesn't wanna invest, you're an unknown. It's too risky!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert furiously grabs the phone.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you know why you're going nowhere in life? Because you've got no imagination. This is like 1966 and you've got an Italian kid on the line by the name of Marty Scorsese - ever heard of him - and you "just don't see it working out." Good luck explaining this to your boss when we premiere. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert hangs up the phone emphatically. A beat of silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's the new president of Miramax.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. THEATER - AN HOUR LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev walks out of the theater. He looks through the glass doors back into the lobby. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew are chatting jovially as Alan walks over to Jimmy. Alan whispers into Jimmy's ear, who nods along. Charlotte walks by the group to the theater entrance and Zev opens the door for her as she approaches.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thanks, have a good night. Sorry we didn't get a chance to talk much. If you start to lose your mind in the lobby, the screening room is a calming reprieve.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, thanks, I'll check it out soon. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Bye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She walks to the curb into a black car waiting for her. Zev watches her be driven away and starts walking toward the subway. Jimmy pokes his head out of theater doors.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey, Zev!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, startled, stops and turns around.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You got five? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(unsure)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Come, let's get your uniform fitted. Tailor's right across the street.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. TAILOR SHOP - MINUTES LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is on an elevated platform in front of a triple mirror getting measured by a TAILOR. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy is watching silently over his shoulder as the tailor continues measuring.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The tailor disappears to the back room and comes back with a tweed jacket. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev’s outfit is revealed: brown tweed suit paired with concession stand paper hat. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy smiles at Zev, who blushes. He turns and steps down. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy looks at him proudly and shakes his hand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Welcome to Cinema Four.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. TAILOR SHOP - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Jimmy are outside. Jimmy lights a cigarette.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stands by silently, unable to hide the newfound pleasure from Jimmy's acceptance.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(extending for a handshake)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well, I'll see you tomorrow. Thank you... </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(glancing down at his outfit)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">for everything.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(mid cigarette pull)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The hell are you on about? We're headed back to the theater. We've got takeout and drinks and the theater to ourselves.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(jokingly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We have the theater to ourselves most of the day... But I should be getting home, the sabbath starts soon. Another time, I promise.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy laughs.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No worries, enjoy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He heads across the street toward the theater and Zev walks in the opposite direction. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">FEBRUARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On a quiet night in the theater, Zev stands behind the concession stand organizing a Mrs. Fields cookie display. He is clearly more comfortable at his post. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A jovial couple exit the screening room, the man pushes her up to the wall, blatantly ignorant to social norms, to give the woman an exaggeratedly romantic kiss. Zev can HEAR a French film playing inside.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy walks in, doing his rounds.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(lifting the bin to Jimmy)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Contraband's running low.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Tell Connie to up the searches. I'll run to the bodega.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy turns away.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey Jim -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he turns back to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What's this movie all about? I can't understand a word.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've never seen </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Breathless?</Text>
<Text Style=""> Go catch the ending! It's a must-see.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy heads to the exit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev removes his cap, places it on the counter, locks the register, and heads to towards the screening room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A crowd of about 12 PEOPLE sit in the dark theater, a mix of geriatrics who consider Jean-Paul Belmondo a contemporary and college-aged kids trying to impress their peers. A crevice of light spills in from the opening of the door to the lobby as Zev slips in. He walks past several empty rows and takes an aisle seat. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CROSSFADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - 45 MINUTES LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is transfixed as the final notes of </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Breathless</Text>
<Text Style="">--featuring NEW YORK HERALD TRIBUNE--play. Zev remains glued as the aisle lights begin to warm up and the meager audience drifts toward the exit. Dazed, Zev looks around the theater, mumbling to himself as the last of the audience shuffles out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The overhead lights burst on and moments later a voice is heard over the intercom. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE (O.S)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank you for coming to Cinema Four. Please make your way to the exit, as the film has concluded. Enjoy the rest of your evening, and please come back again soon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev gets out of his seat, and paces to the middle of the auditorium, looking up in the direction of the projection booth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE (O.S)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(small laugh)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I was starting to worry we had another cadaver on our hands. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(playful)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shawn, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE (O.S)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can hardly hear you. Come on up!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev points in the direction of the exit, looking for affirmation.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. PROJECTION BOOTH - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The projection booth is cramped with boxes so old they could date back to the silent era. Green-walled and cavernous, the back consists entirely of projection equipment and the front has only a small desk atop which sits a lamp--the room's only light source--and various papers. On the wall surrounding the desk are movie schedules and various notes left from technicians and former projectionists.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After a knock on the door, Charlotte opens it and welcomes Zev in as if it were her home.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Welcome! Come in! Don't mind the mess...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte is tidying up items from the table top.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sorry it took me a second... it's like dungeon of darkness coming up here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Those lamps died </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">years</Text>
<Text Style=""> ago. It's a miracle I've never taken a tumble. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd catch you, but I'm not very strong.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's an awkward silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I didn't even realize there were seats up here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's overflow for the orchestra, which has actually only happened when the basement flooded.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte unloads the reel from the projector. She shows Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Isn't she a beauty?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She lets him take a hold of it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wow... I just caught the last half. What did he do? Seemed dramatic, he was stumbling for a while.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've never seen </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Breathless</Text>
<Text Style="">?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I didn't even know it existed until about fifteen minutes ago.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're doing your life a disservice if you've never seen Godard.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I haven't seen that one either. I like movies, but I haven't seen any of the ones you guys show here. A couple of years ago I saw </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Reception, </Text>
<Text Style="">which you probably showed</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">.</Text>
<Text Style=""> I don't remember much besides the buildings went like this. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev makes a bridge with his hands.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(being sweet)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Inception</Text>
<Text Style=""> I think is what it was if I'm remembering correctly</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">.</Text>
<Text Style=""> We've never run it but Mary loves </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Memento</Text>
<Text Style="">. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, we've been hanging out a bit,</Text>
<Text Style="Bold"> </Text>
<Text Style="">with some of the others. They're very nice.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte grins. Theres a short silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I asked about you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh really?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev nods.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary thinks if you don't spend summers sweating in your studio next to the L train, you're missing out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(switching the subject)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Anyway, you should try to catch this from the beginning, we're running it again tomorrow morning.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd like that a lot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. THEATER - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Charlotte exit the theater together. She locks up. Zev starts to walk away from the theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What way are you headed?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh, I'm waiting for my car. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Taking the train out all the way to the west side would take hours, it's just not worth it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev shows some surprise.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You come all the way to Bensonhurst for this?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You'd be surprised, there are so few art house theaters still standing. I'd go practically anywhere besides Staten Island to find a booth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte looks up at the theater marquee.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's really special Alan can keep this old bag alive. But come new year, it's probably the end. There's no way he'll be able to afford the lease renewal.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Isn't there something we could do?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's not us, it's time.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a short silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So you grew up in the city?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Your typical Dalton girl.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I guess that makes me your typical Benny boy. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte laughs.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's pretty good. I like it around here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Bensonhurst?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's just... life. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's changed so much, even since I was a kid. New buildings, new people, new stores. We have pilates now. It's pretty far out. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Time rearing its head around again... and my dad actually built The Avalon Apartments.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah... since I started working at the Four, I've noticed the neighborhood start to shift and I keyed him in. He thinks this could be the next Bushwick - a real haven for artists.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A black car rounds the corner at the end of the street, headed towards the theater. As Charlotte heads to the car, Zev follows to open the door for her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If you liked </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Breathless</Text>
<Text Style=""> you should check out </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Vivre sa v</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">ie</Text>
<Text Style="">. It's my favorite.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Viv-ra say vee</Text>
<Text Style="">? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"My Life to Live."</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd like to think so.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte smiles, and takes a seat in the car.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Goodnight, it was nice to formally meet you. Stop by the booth anytime; I mean it Benny boy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev smiles and starts to close the door.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Uh, where do I watch the movie?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You can use my Criterion login. When you're through </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Vivre</Text>
<Text Style="">, just start going through the classics and you'll understand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the driver)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thomas, a pen?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte takes hold of Zev's arm and writes down her email and password on his forearm. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thanks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The car takes off down the road. Zev watches it for a second, then turns and strides down the empty street.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S ROOM - LATER </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Vivre s</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">a v</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">ie </Text>
<Text Style="">is playing on Zev's TV. He looks befuddled, but intrigued.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The entire crew, minus Charlotte, is seated around the circular lounge in the center of the lobby. There are beers, bottles of wine, and boxes of Chinese take-out sprawled across floor. The crew are waiting patiently to begin the meal.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, it’s tradition on nights like this for someone to say a few words. We either take stock of our privilege, mourn an injustice in the world, or just express gratitude that we’re alive. And as the newest member of the group, we’d like you to do the honors tonight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(blushing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let me think for a second...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's stalling. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(friendly jab)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Just like Jimmy when we ask him to read one of his poems.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If I wanted to write </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Milk &amp; Honey </Text>
<Text Style="">maybe I'd have something for you, but I'm working on my magnum opus.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ignoring Jimmy, stalling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Should we wait for Charlotte?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE &amp; WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oooooh.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you guys not like her?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She's a Manhattan girl, and we're Brooklynites. There's nothing bad about that per se; not everyone wants to be authentic.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Speak for yourself. She cost us some serious cash. She's practically eviscerated Zev's first dozen checks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Huh?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(immediately)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Heads down everyone... Zev go ahead.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The rest of the group close their eyes and bow their heads. Zev takes a long pause and closes his eyes as well.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(reciting softly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shalom aleichem, malachei hashareit, malachei elyon, mimelech malchei ham'lachim, hakadosh baruch hu. Boachem l'shalom, malachei hashalom, mal -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ending the prayer short)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ahmen!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev opens his eyes in surprise, having only done half the prayer. All of the crew are moving to fill their plates with food.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(exhale, deeply moved)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wow, what was that?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My torah portion, what I can remember at least. It's been a while since Hebrew school, but some of it just melds to your brain for life.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quietly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Indoctrination...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What does it mean?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Um, something like, "Peace be to you, ministering angels, messengers of the Most High, the supreme Sovereign, the Holy, and the Blessed One."</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So you're an Israelite?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We're really sorry about... all that. We had the Great Depression, but, you, I couldn't imagine.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh... no. It's fine. My family's been here for generations.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(trying to lighten the mood)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My great, great grandfather was the accountant for the Mayflower.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(impressed)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So you're a real Brooklyn guy. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You don't really talk like one.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The neighborhood is pretty yuppie now, so I never really picked it up. My parents have it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Gentrifiers.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You must love </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The Lords of Flatbush</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(taking a guess)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My parents were pretty strict with what I watched as a kid...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(hesitant)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If... you're ever free on a Friday night, my family does a dinner. You'd probably like my dad, he's more of that real </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Brooklyn</Text>
<Text Style=""> type of guy you're talking about. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We'd love that.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group agrees, then digs into the food.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is standing in the concession stand with Robert, Warren, and Connie, pouring himself a drink from the soda fountain. Warren tops Zev's cup off with a healthy pour of cheap schnapps.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Stop stop stop. What you're saying to me is, you haven't seen </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The Godfather</Text>
<Text Style="">? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I think I've probably seen it, but it was years ago. I remember a horse's head and guy with these big cheeks -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And who was he?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The Godfather. I'm not sure of who though, do we ever find that out?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(playful)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No it's a big secret. Do you remember his name?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can't remember. Something with a "D"? Donald maybe?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes, Donald, exactly! Are you sure you haven't seen it recently? And he has a son.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">His son in the movie or real life?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sarcastic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">In real life, Marlon Brando yeah. No, in the movie!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm sorry, I don't remember him as a major character. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You have to watch Part 2 for that.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's two of them?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren and Connie are giggling.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Three, if you can believe it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The film community would disagree.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie, Warren, Robert, and Jimmy are in the main screening room of the theater. </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Fast Times at Ridgemont High</Text>
<Text Style=""> is playing on the projector, without sound, and they are dancing to the soundtrack, which is PLAYING over the loud speaker.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The scene from the movie in which Cinema Four is referenced comes on screen and the entire crew CLAP and CHEER.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy stops dancing, skips to the screening room door, and pokes his head out. The MUSIC spills into the lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary and Zev are cleaning up the food and drink. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(calling to them)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Get in here!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary and Zev, with trash bags in their hands look over.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh I love this song. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(she puts down the bags)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let's go.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She tugs Zev's arm, who puts down his trash bag and gets pulled to the screening room. Zev is reluctant at first, but Mary gives him another tug.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">C'mon, you're one of us.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev smiles and follows her, disappearing behind the screening room door. The MUSIC can still be heard, now more quietly, in the empty lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">MARCH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - EVENING </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is behind the counter placing a few new boxes of snacks under the glass. Warren is lying on the lobby couch reading through a script. Connie walks up to the counter. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's Mary's birthday tonight, we're going to throw a surprise party at her place. We're meeting Jimmy at Party City.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm not sure I can hang tonight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What?! You have to!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(leaning in a little)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We got her a cake.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh, well - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(still reading)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You can't miss a birthday. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't have a gift or anything.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Volunteer for the photo wall, if you have an inkling for exhibitionism.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(slightly confused)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alright... let me close out the register and I'll meet you by the train.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(smiling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay deal!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie and Warren walk towards their cubbies together as Zev watches them disappear. He then frantically fills and fastens a lid to a large soda cup and rummages for a bag of Finnish Fish beneath the counter, ensuring no one is watching him. Confident that the coast is clear, he slips out from behind the counter and up to the projection room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. MARY'S APARTMENT, LIVING ROOM - NIGHT </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">All the lights are off. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Party favors half-assedly hang from the walls of the apartment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group is sprawled across the living room in various hiding spots.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Connie are crouched down behind the couch. Behind them, on the wall, are a set of photographs. They are of male's thighs and penises. Zev is examining them with Connie. They are speaking in whispers.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She's really got an eye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary took those?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy overhears them talking and scoots over to them from his hiding spot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I came up with the idea.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's brilliant. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">When's the last time you went to the Met and saw a room full of Richards? Never. And when you finally see David, he's got the pecker of a school boy. I'm no art historian but I'd be real surprised if Michelangelo's ever painted flat-chested woman. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've been to the Met on a middle school trip, I remember they had these little turkey sandwiches that we got for free. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If we want to get past the way  bodies are objectified in society we need to destroy the phallic fallacy. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Where does Mary find her subjects?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Friends and family mostly. That's Jimmy and... that's Robert. She'll probably ask you at one point, once you're more comfortable. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary’s key scrapes against the lock and the door lurches open.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ooh shh! She's coming!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary comes into the living room and flips the lights on. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY, ZEV, CONNIE, WARREN, ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Surprise!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group blows KAZOOs and POPs confetti. Mary jumps with surprise and glee.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. MARY'S APARTMENT, LIVING ROOM - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary is sitting on the floor, wearing a birthday sash and tiara. Warren is next to her, adorned in party favors. Robert and Jimmy have some tassels and other birthday gear. Zev is favor-less, as he eats a slice of pizza.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">All I'm trying to say is that in a profit-driven society, your brain doesn't get a chance to ponder the bigger questions of existence. If we equalized society, then we could be free to come into ourselves and create real art.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(argumentative, to Mary)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Equality is just not equipped to produce art. Art is a response to the ills of society. Imagine a world without crack cocaine. What would Keith Haring have done with that mural? What's Mapplethorpe up to without AIDS? In your utopia, we'd all be doing claymation.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(under her breath, to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wait until he discovers the Brothers Quay.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev nods in agreement.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(at Connie)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">I</Text>
<Text Style=""> know the Quay! And there's no way, the Quay use clay! Stick to </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Chicken Run.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary's eye's perk up.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The pies!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She runs into the kitchen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What about the Soviet Union? A completely classless society. Minds were able to ponder and wonder without the burden of </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">ego</Text>
<Text Style="">. All they had was the </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">id</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">.</Text>
<Text Style=""> That's the world that gave us Andrei Tarkovsky, the greatest poet to ever point a lens. He didn't make films to sleep with hookers in the Hollywood Hills. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What a crock of shit. The only thing they were looking for in the "zone" was a goddamn Chase Bank.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary rushes back into the living room holding two apple pies.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The hard truth is that a man sees the female artist and thinks, "wow, we're going to have so much to talk about after sex". And a woman sees the male artist and thinks, "wow we're going to have so much to talk about during dinner." </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What about Van Gogh? Poor guy wasn't hot until he was six feet under for a century. He was so horned up by the end, he chopped his ear off just to feel something.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Sam Kitterman" DateTime="20220315T123911">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Maybe just change it up, I see Jimmy's comment below</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">He was a handsome one too. Imagine, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Starry Night </Text>
<Text Style="">on an easel in his bedroom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(she shudders with glee)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So you're trying to say a painting gives you more pleasure than the saps you drag back here? That </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">acrylic</Text>
<Text Style=""> is dry, baby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. MARY'S APARTMENT, FOYER - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It is later in the evening. Warren is grabbing his coat. Zev is passing through from the kitchen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're headed out?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm headed up for a smoke on the roof. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the living room)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Anyone game?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Absolutely.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't want to smoke a full one, Robby, can we split?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I was going to sprinkle some dust on mine, but you're free to ride along.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't go to Mars, please, we're supposed to run lines after this. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Relax, we already did lines.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Everyone besides Mary groups in the foyer. Zev turns back to Mary as the group is halfway out the door. He pauses in the doorway.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're not coming?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary you're not coming?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No babe, don't worry about it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don’t want to leave Mary alone here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No it's alright, that's sweet of you for asking. I don't have the vice privilege, not even second-hand. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stares blankly at her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Take a billionaire and a man sleeping on the street. When the rich man gets stressed or tired or wants some euphoria, he can get a massage or go to Mohegan Sun. Have you ever seen a homeless person at Mohegan Sun?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've never been to a Mohegan Sun.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The poor man's options for a smile are dope, cigarettes, and cheap alcohol. All of which are detrimental. The rich man's "vices" are all beneficial, or at the very least, in his control. And therefore, it's completely absurd that those of us that are aware of our privilege would engage in vices reserved for those less fortunate. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But don't we all drink?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you know how many antioxidants are in a glass of red wine?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stares at Mary, unsure.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Really, it's fine.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is uneasy but follows the rest out of the door, leaving Mary alone in the foyer. She starts cleaning up.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">EXT. MOVIE THEATER - MORNING</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is standing outside the theater, waiting. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A black Mercedes pulls up and Charlotte gets out of the car. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev lights up as she meets him by the entrance.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh hey - no keys? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She smiles and unlocks the door.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The two stop at the crossroads between the concessions counter and the projection booth. Charlotte turns to Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If you like French New Wave... oh, I know, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The 400 Blows</Text>
<Text Style="">. That's essential viewing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(with a smile)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm on it. Sorry, I'm still using your account, I watch something new almost every night.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(mimicking Peter Sellers)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"There's no fighting in here, this is the war room!"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte laughs, touching his arm softly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Classic, you're a natural. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(talking low)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know, tonight's last movie ends pretty early. If you don't have anything going on, I could play </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The 400 Blows</Text>
<Text Style=""> for you here. It really deserves the silver screen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd like that a lot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte waves goodbye and heads to the stairs, up to the balcony.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev gets behind the counter and puts on his concession stand hat. He looks excited.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stands behind the concession stand, anxious, sporadically looking at a clock on the wall as it ticks towards closing time. He counts the night's earnings, continuously losing track and having to start over.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew get packed up and begin heading home. Zev, still fiddling with the takings from the stand, perks up at the prospect of everyone leaving.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Cya, kid.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Not hanging out tonight?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nah, Mary's ducking out east to her family's place. And I've got a date. Been a while, so throw me a mazel if you've got any extras. We'll be back at it next week though.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev nods, hiding his pleasure at the news.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They say GOODBYEs and all exit the theater, leaving Zev alone. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A NOISE by the stairs indicates Charlotte is descending from the projection room, but her arrival in the lobby coincides with The General also arriving from the screening room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Get down!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev quickly hides behind the concession counter as The General emerges into the lobby with a broom and pale.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The hoi polloi have left the building!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to The General)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm just about to lock up...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He jumps into a salute and heads to the door. At the entrance he stops and turns back to Charlotte. He pulls out his flashlight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Perimeter duty. We can't let the Kong breach the hill. Not on my watch.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He exits the theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. THEATER - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The General walks away from the theater pointing his flashlight at various objects and people.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He flashes around a bus stop, ridden with graffiti and profanity.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(squinting)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hm... hieroglyphics...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He takes out a field notebook and begins to scribble down what he sees.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev crawls out from behind the concession stand. Charlotte is standing near him, smiling.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's quite the wildcard, makes me nervous.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">the</Text>
<Text Style=""> case study on the dangers of method acting.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's playing a character?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">In 1990, The General scored an audition for Malick's comeback film, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The Thin Red Line.</Text>
<Text Style=""> It was gonna be his big break, so The General went full method. But, 1990 became '91, then '92, '93, '95, and goodbye. The General became The General for good. I don't even know his real name. Neither does he, anymore.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(standing up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you think he saw me?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He would've called in an airstrike by now. I'm going to run and get set up. Can you turn off the house lights?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev watches her jog up the stairs and moves to the light switches, killing them all and shrouding the lobby in darkness, lit only by the radiance of the soda machine. He fixes each of them a soda.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">DANKE SCHOEN begins to play, softly, over the theater's speaker system. Before he heads up the stairs, he fills two small bags with stale popcorn, douses them with Flavacol, and tucks a box of candy in his back pocket.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev jogs to the top of the stairs, and pauses a minute to catch his breath. He walks up to the projection booth door and gives it a KNOCK. A second later the door opens, Charlotte inside fiddling with the projection equipment and holding the door open with her foot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(smiling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Refreshments.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank you. Get comfortable.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte removes her foot from the door and it begins to fall closed. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh are you not --</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The door SLAMS shut in his face. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev proceeds down the balcony steps, taking a seat on the top row, directly under the projector. He sits down and gets comfortable. He sneaks a few glances up at the projector window to see if Charlotte is looking at him. She is not. The projector clicks on and the OPENING NOTES of </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The 400 Blows </Text>
<Text Style="">begin to play. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev's face reveals disappointment that he'll be viewing alone. He settles in to watch and about 15 seconds later the projection booth door is heard opening and closing. Zev looks to his right and sees Charlotte descending the steps to where he's sitting, taking the seat next to his. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They watch the opening of the movie. As Zev peeks at Charlotte he sees her doing the same. He keeps his eyes forward, rubbing his sweaty palms on his trousers.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte crosses her legs, which causes her foot to brush Zev's calf. She doesn't move it away.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After a moment of consideration, Zev grabs her hand. She squeezes back, and as the soundtrack to the film crescendos they both settle in to watch the movie, hand-in-hand. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - AN HOUR AND A HALF LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As the final notes of the film play, Zev and Charlotte are arm-in-arm, making out. The sounds of the ocean from the film play in the background.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO BLACK.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">SEPTEMBER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - AFTERNOON </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The entire staff is in Alan's office. Zev and Charlotte are seated next to each other.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">DAKOTAH (early 20s) tall, handsome and tan, wearing a suit, walks in. He and Mary's eyes meet, and Mary is thrown off momentarily.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He smiles at the group, and then walks to Alan's side.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Everyone, the dark days are over.  Remember I told you I was working on bringing in some operational expertise? Well, here he is! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He stands to shake Dakotah's hand. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T223700">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">down for that</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">We've been selected as an "at risk business" for Dartmouth's MBA Consultancy Practicum. They've graciously sent us one of their best...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking down at a note)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is "nearly at the top of his cohort, majoring in the business of entertainment." He's here to get to know us and give us some ideas for the future. He's nobody's boss, but he's got my ear, and I'm listening.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(embracing Alan)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank you for the kind words. It's truly a privilege to come here and work with you all. Before I dive in, I want to address the elephant in the room. It's never been an issue in the past, and I don't expect it to be one now...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pausing to look over the staff and smiles)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T223651">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Yeah like he is not montgomery clift's grandson by blood, thats the humor, if its funny is up for debate but that was the attempt</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">I can already see the gears turning... "he looks familiar, where do I know that face?" The answer is </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">A Place Under The Sun -</Text>
<Text Style=""> I am the grandson of Montgomery Clift. Now I want to be clear, that does not mean I can call up Monty to come save the theater; he's dead. I do things on my own accord, and I'm going to turn this place around with sound business practices, hard work, and a bit of help from all of you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a short pause, then it's obvious that he has finished his speech. Alan claps and the rest of the staff halfheartedly join in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Post-meeting, Alan is giving Dakotah a tour of the lobby. Dakotah is holding a clipboard. Alan leads Dakotah over to Zev at the concession stand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Here's our other newbie, less than a year, doesn't feel like it huh?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(chuckling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe Zev has some interesting thoughts for you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's great. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(handshake with Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah Clift.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev Stern.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(chummy)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You gotta show me the ropes Zev. I see the stand as a big part of our success. What we have here is a closed system, like an airport. Once the customer is in, you're their only source of nourishment. We crank up the heat and fix the Slurpee machine, I can already see massive potential.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan is clearly a big fan of Dakotah, very impressed.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We have a "no outside snacks" policy and we conduct random searches at the rope. They're not so random really.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Alan)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Psh! This guy. You don't need me here! Business tycoon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's kismet!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy walks through the lobby. Alan sees him and jumps to chat with him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jim! Hold on a second. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Dakotah and Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Talk, talk, I'll be back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan leaves the two of them. As he walks away, Dakotah turns to watch the lobby with his back against the concession counter.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(taking in his new domain)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Starving artists. Well, not you, Zev. You’ve got it all figured out back here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm not an artist, Robert and Warren are working on a film, Jimmy's a poet, Mary's done some phenomenal portraits, and I'm not 100% sure what Connie does.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't sell yourself short.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he turns to face Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've got... </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">something</Text>
<Text Style="">. I could feel it in that room. Leadership. You just need vision, passion, and drive, and your wildest dreams will follow.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev's drawn in by Dakotah's charm.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(blushing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, maybe. I've gotten pretty into cinema myself. Not as much as the rest of the crew, but -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(turning back toward the lobby)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Imagine Vanderbilt, laying in bed.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a baron's accent)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"There's going to be a railroad running through every city worth its salt!"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(back to normal)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Then he woke up, and he built it; Dreams to reality.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(not fully buying it)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I think it was mostly the Chinese who built the track, he just paid for it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah whips around to face Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Exactly! And look at them now, taking over the world! Impressive stuff.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah leans back to survey the lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He places a hand over Zev's hands on the concession counter.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This place is a lump of coal... and I'm going to make it a diamond.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, LIVING ROOM -  AFTERNOON</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T222554">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">agreed</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">MRS. SHERYL STERN (60s) with heavy makeup, pearl earnings, and a fur coat is sitting on the couch in the living room watching television. The room is modestly kitsch, unchanged from the 1970s.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The doorbell RINGS. Sheryl immediately props herself up, wanting to look good for her incoming guests. No one immediately goes to open door.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(yelling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo! Get the door!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev comes through the hallway to the door. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T222603">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">agreed</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">He opens it, revealing Jimmy, Robert, Connie, Warren, and Mary waiting outside. They are all dressed nicely. Jimmy is holding a plastic-wrapped shrimp cocktail.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can't believe you actually showed up...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, DINING ROOM - MINUTES LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">An extended dining table is covered with a beautiful patterned tablecloth. Around the periphery sit the crew, the men in outsized and obviously borrowed yarmulkes. At the head of the table sits Sheryl, flanked by her son and her husband SHLOMO STERN (60s) in a white dress shirt half buttoned, with a tank top and star of David chain visible underneath. He has a traditional New York-Yiddish hybrid accent and talks exuberantly with the crew while his wife breaths in wine. There is one seat and place setting next to Zev that is empty.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Mr. / Mrs. Stern)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Again, we're terribly sorry about the shrimp cocktail, we had no idea. It was so inappropriate, we feel terrible.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nonsense! You were never briefed! Zevvy has always had that special  non-attention to detail.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew slurp up every last facet of their environment, excited to be in surroundings so different from their own. Zev, meanwhile, pouts quietly on the sidelines, embarrassed and regretful for inviting everyone.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Start already, they're starving!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alright, alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo stands.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I hope Zev told you, we don't do the rituals much anymore, but he told us "give them the authentic experience!" It's Sunday, not Friday, so we've already missed the mark on that, but no worries, in about thirty minutes, Zevvy will be crying, she'll be off the 'shevitz, and I can give you all a ride to the J. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dad, please.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay, first we light the candles. We're just going to use the menorah because we couldn't find a candle holder, but this is what we use on </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hanukkah so it's all still very Jewish. Don't worry.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo lights two candles in the menorah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the crew)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Like this - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He waves his hands in front of his face three times and covers his eyes. Everyone mimics him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO, SHERYL, ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(singing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Barukh atah Adonai Eloheinu melekh ha’olam asher kid’shanu b’mitzvotav v’tzivanu l’hadlik ner shel shabbat</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A moment of silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You can open your eyes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew is thoroughly enjoying the show.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That was beautiful.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zevvy, sing </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Shalom Aleichem</Text>
<Text Style=""> with your father. It's been years, it's a special night. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mom, please -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We want to hear it, Zevvy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">C'mon!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev resigns. He gets up and stands next to his father.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We are welcoming the angels to our home, to our dinner, on this beautiful night together... one, two, three, </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(silently mouths "four")</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO, ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(singing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T222651">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">yeah thats fine</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="Italic">Shalom aleichem mal’achei hashareit mal’achei elyon. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Mimelech malchei...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The doorbell RINGS, interrupting the singing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No one gets up to get it and the crew look at Shlomo, Zev, and Sheryl, confused as to why no one is answering the door. The Sterns stare back blankly</Text>
<Text Style="Bold">. </Text>
<Text Style="">A few moments pass.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the air)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh I'd love for a bit of a breeze. I wish just by chance maybe the door would open. If only the door would fly open by some sort of happenstance.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew is confused.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering, to the crew)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We can't work after sundown.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the air)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh how I'd just love for a nice </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">gentile</Text>
<Text Style=""> breeze to open the door.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a silence. Warren gets up uncertainly</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I guess I can get it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the air)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh thank you so much, what a great idea you thought of. Bless you, mazel my dear boy!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, FOYER - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren opens the door to see Charlotte, holding a bottle of wine, and a taxi driving off behind her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sweetly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hi.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(surprised)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh, hi... I didn't know you were on the guest list.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte walks past him inside.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, DINING ROOM - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte enters the dining room followed by Warren. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sheryl is passing out bowls of matzah ball soup.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(surprised)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Woah!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew look up to see Charlotte. They are stunned. They look at Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to her hosts)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm sorry I'm late. I'm Charlotte. Thank you so much for having me.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(handing the bottle to Shlomo)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It one of my father's favorites.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte holds the bottle out in front of her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T222805">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">he could just come over and take it happily, we can discuss</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">Oh, what a lovely gift! Thank you, thank you! Shlomo Stern. A pleasure, please sit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte takes her seat in the empty chair next to Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Here you are sweetie, I'll get you a soup. How many balls?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Uh... two please.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary exchanges looks with Jimmy. She pours him and herself glasses of wine, and then hovers over Charlotte's glass.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm sure it's not as good as what you brought.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's quite alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary pours her a full glass, to the brim.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sheryl comes back with the soup and places it front of Charlotte.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(mockingly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Just like Sadelles.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy smiles slyly at the joke. Charlotte does not dignify it with a response. Robert, Warren, and Connie are exchanging looks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I grew up with Benny Sadelle. We used to cut school together and catch a matinee at The Avalon. In the morning, he would stop at the Respoli's, get a bag of rainbow cookies - and it wasn't about a movement back then, that's just how they made them. He'd come into my bed with his feet at my head, completely kosher, and we'd sleep until about three or four. Then we would walk down to 15th Street and watch a picture</Text>
<Text Style="Italic"> </Text>
<Text Style="">and eat our rainbow cookies. I remember when I was 12, I snuck in to </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Bullitt</Text>
<Text Style="">. With Steve McQueen, I bet you kids don't even know that movie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(interrupting)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">1968, Peter Yates.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(surprised)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, I'm almost certain it was McQueen...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(continuing his story)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But, I'll never forget there was an Albanian woman in the back of the theater who would stroke your thigh for a nickel, and for a dime she'd rub your back and say she was proud of you... I miss the old 'Bush. It was all candy stores, delis, and dentists. Now its coffee shops, Korean foot spas, and coffee shops. Who needs so much coffee and acupuncture?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking at Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I heard The Avalon was beautiful, it's a shame they tore it down and built that horrid apartment complex.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev sees Mary looking at Charlotte. Charlotte doesn't flinch, staying completely composed and silent. She affectionately rubs Zev's hand under the table.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On Tuesday nights, they had an open mic in the lobby, and me, Benny Sadelle, and Willy Katz were a trio called "Home Before Sundown".</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It must've been incredible back then. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(slightly slurring)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It was a complete bore! Everything fun was in Manhattan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What'd do you know about fun? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If you'd made anything of yourself you wouldn't be rotting here, yapping on about all you did with those boys. They became successful men, and you?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A father to a beautiful boy!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ignoring his comment)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you think they dream about you as much as you do of them?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo retracts, his demeanor shifts from happy and friendly to genuinely upset. There is a long, uncomfortable silence at the table.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(coming to his defense)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Woody Allen is from Flatbush. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo lets out a WAIL.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(fed up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You mean that pervert who made a movie called </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Manhattan</Text>
<Text Style="">?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(nostalgic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh, I miss Heywood. He had </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">something</Text>
<Text Style="">, we knew it since the beginning. You have your dreamers </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(gesturing to Shlomo)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And your doers. He was both.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo abruptly gets up from the table. He looks at his guests.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(composing himself)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shabbat Shalom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He walks out of the room. The air is awkward. Sheryl gulps down her wine.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shabbat Shalom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(concerned)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Was that - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(upset)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't mind him, sweetie, he had his chances...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(blushing, teary-eyed)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So did I.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I feel awful.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You bring up a monster during a religious ceremony and think it's going work out?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sheryl abruptly gets up from the table.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quivering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shabbat Shalom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She abruptly exits. An awkward silence falls on the room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Should we leave?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, no. We have to at least finish the soup. Here...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He gets up and goes over to a record player in the living room. He puts in a vinyl of a Hebrew album. It starts to PLAY. He returns to his seat and restarts eating his soup. The group follows, eating and listening to the music without speaking.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, FOYER - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy, Robert, Mary, Connie, Warren, Charlotte, and Zev are at the door. All but Zev and Charlotte have their coat on.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy places his hand on Zev's shoulder.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank's for having us. Really, it was a pleasure.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sorry for this, I should've known.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert pats Jimmy on the back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No way man, it was an experience.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev smiles meekly. He opens the door for them and all but Charlotte go outside. Jimmy notices Charlotte still inside.  </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte, trying to be nice)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Should we wait for your car?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm going to drive her in when traffic settles down.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy's eyes flash between the two of them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We'll see you two tomorrow then. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy gives Zev a look and then a mock salute before Zev closes the door. He jogs to catch up with the rest of the crew.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What the hell was that?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(resigned)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shabbat shalom. Fuck me. Zev must've told her there was some special babka waiting.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(gesturing to Robert)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We gotta catch the bus, we're supposed to be on set in thirty.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What set?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(stoic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My apartment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're still working on Yobification? Hasn't it been like four years?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(irritated)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hold on let me give you Linklater's number, he can tell you a thing or two about how long it takes to make a masterpiece. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group reaches an intersection, Robert and Warren heading in one direction and the rest of the crew in another.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S HOUSE, DINING ROOM - LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Charlotte sits with arms entwined, utterly oblivious to anything except one another. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I should've known...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It was my fault.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My mom hates that I took the job at the theater. She say's there's no future in scooping popcorn.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's never too late to make something of yourself. Manoel de Oliveira didn't make it until his 70s. Unfortunately not everyone can be Orson Welles. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">When did he make it?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well... he happened to make the greatest film of all time at 25. But you don't need to make the greatest anything. You should do whatever takes your mind off the fact that our world is filled with genocides, our farms with pesticides, and your parents don't love each other anymore.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking Charlotte in the eyes)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't think of any of those things when I'm with you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She smiles and stares back at him. They kiss.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you know it's a mitzvah -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">OCTOBER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">INT.  THEATER LOBBY - AFTERNOON </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is standing next to Alan as NATHAN, a chubby boy in his early 20s with high functioning Aspergers and an Oakland Athletics hat, replaces movie posters in the lobby, which show the current slate of the theater. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev watches from the concession stand as Mary, Jimmy, Warren, Robert and Connie walk into the theater carrying lunch. Mary, holding a large brown paper bag, drops it immediately as she lays eyes on Nathan and his armful of posters.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What the fuck?! Why is money-ball touching my slate??</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Marianne, be nice. This is my protégé Nathan, a close confidant of mine from Dartmouth. He's got just the plan to give us a boost in Q4. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Everyone besides Nathan registers the tension in the air.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(casually)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">With Dakotah's help, I ran a SWOT analysis on the theater's most profitable demographic. Starting Monday we are going to run: </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Midnight Cowboy</Text>
<Text Style="">, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Beau Travail</Text>
<Text Style="">, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Brokeback Mountain</Text>
<Text Style="">, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Fox and His Friends</Text>
<Text Style="">, and a rotating hit from the Marvel Universe. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now that's a lineup. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Alan)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What did I tell you?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(trembling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This is a joke right? Alan? Robert? Anyone? Marvel? Should we just bend over and let you fuck us, or how do you want to do this?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, please, you're still our curator, you always will be, but we want a fresh pair of - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(cutting Alan off)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's a genius Mary, trust me. We still want to hear your thoughts, but hear Nathan out. He's really onto something revolutionary.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Uh, well my research shows young, closeted jock homosexuals in their early teens struggle with distinguishing other gays from the rest boys on the team. So many mixed signals in the locker room, it's impossible to tell when a pat on bum or a light kiss on the lips is just praise for a job well done or something more. So, with this slate, they can say, "hey brother wanna go see </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Green Lantern</Text>
<Text Style=""> and some other movie, they're doing a double header?" Takes away all the pressure. By the time the house lights come on after </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Brokeback Mountain</Text>
<Text Style="">, if they're both flushed, that's great. Ultimately, he just wants to know if they're on the same team.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary is in utter disbelief. Her eyes well up and she wipes them, blushing heavily.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(voice crackling)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Haven't we learned our lesson about double headers?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She quickly picks up the grocery bag and the assorted items that spilled and walks out of the theater. After a few moments of stunted silence, Connie runs out of the theater to catch up with her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Feels pretty predatory. I'm not comfortable with exploiting today's gay youth for profit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he ponders)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On the other hand, it is a nice night out for two boys filled with curiosity and a couple bucks to spare.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No one responds to his comment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(breaking the silence)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But why are all these films Uranian? I'd imagine quite a few girls on the softball team may want a crack at this too.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You are absolutely correct, though I wouldn't necessarily call them Uranian. Besides, the fact is women are </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">much</Text>
<Text Style=""> more perceptive at that age. In any four season city, young girls automatically know "a beanie past May means you're absolutely gay."</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's right, my niece... we were on Coney Island in August and she just refused to take the damn thing off.  Sure as a black night's sky, she brings a girl to Thanksgiving.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No one responds. Nathan continues putting up the posters. Jimmy eyes the door, then looks to Robert and Warren, contemplating a walk-out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte, who was watching from the stairwell, comes into the lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Give him a chance, we can't be doing any worse. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm a little worried about having a bunch of boys around here with The General, he might round up Dorothy's friends and start a platoon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ah, yes. That was the other announcement. The payroll just can't sustain a full staff, and, well, you tell me who should go instead of him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew look to Alan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Isn't he's a volunteer?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">In business, he's what we call a </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">liability.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(meekly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's what we need to survive. The greater good. He'll be alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The General walks into the doorway with his pail and broom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Attennnntion.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(he stays in a salute)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The room is silent. The General looks at the crew's faces. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy walks over and gives him a big hug and a pat on the back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sincerely)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank you for your service. You've been dismissed. We've won the war.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The General is in disbelief.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(tears streaming down his face)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Has Saigon fallen?!! I can't believe it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. MARY'S HAMPTONS HOUSE - EARLY MORNING</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary sits alone on a stone bench in the garden of her parents’ lush Southampton home. Bedraggled with purple crescents beneath her eyes, she smokes a cigarette and swigs from a near-empty bottle of red wine.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She hears the gravel of the long driveway CHURN as a 90s Range Rover pulls up to the front of the house.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She watches as her father, RICHARD, early 60s, grey hair, but in great shape for his age, exits the house to approach the car. He is dressed in white shorts and a white polo, carrying a tennis racket and bag.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary sees a man step out of the car, also wearing white shorts and a white polo. They embrace. Neither look over to the garden where Mary is seated.  </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The two men have a short, inaudible discussion, before the visitor quickly hops into the driver seat of his car, grabs his racket, and removes the keys, before joining Richard in his Mercedes G Wagon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As they leave, they stop close to Mary and roll down the driver's side window, revealing Dakotah in the passenger seat.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We have a doubles match against the O'Briens. We'll be back for dinner. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The two smile and wave as they pull off. Mary waits until the car has left before she drifts over to the pool. There are several empty wine bottles scattered near the sun-beds. She peers at her reflection from the pool’s edge, then turns away and lets her body fall backwards into the water, holding out her cigarette to protect it. Like a corpse she floats lifelessly with her eyes closed, taking an occasional drag.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Her mother, FLORENCE, early 50s, well-dressed and well-mannered, casually approaches the pool. She is completely unfazed by Mary being in the water.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Daddy is inviting Dakotah to stay for dinner, the Clifts are out East. I called William, he's bringing his new wife. So be ready by seven.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary flips over to be face first in the water. Florence walks away. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. MARY'S HAMPTONS HOUSE, DINING ROOM - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A long dining table sits in the middle of a tastefully decorated dining room. Seated at the furthest end of the table is Richard, with Florence to his left and Mary next to her. Mary has clearly attempted to clean herself up after a long day of drinking, but her anguish shows. To Richard's right is WILLIAM CLIFT JR., a handsome man in his 50s, followed by TATYANA, mid 30s, Russian and covered in jewelry. Dakotah is to her left, directly across from Mary.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The table is jammed with terrines of food and empty plates, interspersed with wine and champagne bottles. Everyone is sated, apart from Mary who’s perched solemnly on the periphery of the conversation, absently playing with a full plate of food in front of her as the others talk. As the dinner progresses, Mary consistently puts back glasses of wine.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WILLIAM CLIFT JR.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What can I say, love is love.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He puts his arm around Tatyana.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Aww.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She puts her hand over Richard's, warmly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now every time I come out East, it's pierogi's and borscht, but honestly, it's not bad.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to William, curtly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What's an all-American guy doing with a soviet Elizabeth Taylor? Flo can give you our psychiatrist.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(fierce)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Marianne how dare you!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TATYANA</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in Russian, to Mary)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">I'm a spy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WILLIAM CLIFT JR.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(cracking up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She says she's a spy!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group except Mary laugh mightily. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Richard stands to pour more champagne into Tatyana's glass. He looks to Dakotah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How are you managing at the theater, regretting it yet? At this point, the land is worth more than anything inside. Could do a full demo and build something more befitting of the times. Maybe a food court?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes! After we dropped Mary off, Richard was starved. We went to one of those "Taste the World" cafeterias in Downtown Brooklyn. It was so authentic. A group of homeless came in when it rained, but I'm sure they'll sort that out in time.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ah I don't think that's what I'm after. The theater is iconic. Last resort, we'll have to try for historical landmark status. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now that's clever. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary rolls her eyes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If all goes well, the only food available will be stale popcorn and Red Vines. Just in these last few weeks getting to know Alan, I think he'd rather die broke than see the hard hats come in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd be weary of that type of thinking. Every man has his limits.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They've come before. We don't need Dakotah's business wizardry to turn the Four into another beer hall for Brooklyn yuppies.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm sure Dakotah has a plan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WILLIAM CLIFT JR.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll make a call. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dad! No. We don't need a call.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah, your privilege is your power. Never be ashamed of what your family can do for you. They earned it. You got that job on merit, right? Now use what's in your arsenal and help this poor man and his theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Actually, it was Charlotte who introduced me to Alan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary's eyes widen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Fuckin' slimy bitch. I knew this was all too convenient. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLORENCE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh little Charlotte Ladue! She was priceless. I must call her mother and set up dinner. Mary, do you remember when you used to babysit, and you couldn't stand her?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RICHARD</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in between gulps of whisky)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary - Mary used to say, "for $17 dollars an hour, I'd rather be epileptic." </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(bursts out laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've changed so much honey... ahh maybe it was Mount Holyoke...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary pushes her chair away from the table, finishes her glass of wine in one chug, and walks away, out the door, shutting it with force. There's an awkward silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. MARY'S HAMPTONS HOUSE - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary is standing in the foyer in front of the house, staring out into space. A cigarette is in her mouth, unlit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She hears the front door OPEN and FOOTSTEPs, as Dakotah cautiously approaches her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He offers her a light, she leans forward and accepts it, taking a drag with the cigarette tip in the flame. Once the cigarette is lit, she looks at him and exhales a drag. She puts the cigarette back to her lips with a shaky hand. Cigarette in mouth, she lets out a whimper and a cough. She continues coughing, which morphs into a full-blown sob.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She jerks away and stumbles onto the gravel driveway, leaving Dakotah on the porch. He looks on with concern as she heads to a Mini Cooper, parked amongst the fleet of expensive cars in the driveway.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(calling out)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, what are you doing?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She doesn't stop or turn around and continues to wobble toward the car.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(scream)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(blubbering scream)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh fuck you! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She gets into the car.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As Mary turns on the engine, Dakotah rushes over to the car and stands in front of it. Putting his hands on the hood.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(loudly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's going to be okay.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">From inside the car, Mary has turned on the RADIO loud enough to drown out what Dakotah is saying. She can only see his mouth move, as the RADIO drowns out everything he says. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Get out of the fucking way! Leave me alone!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah sees Mary yelling but can't hear anything over the music. She eventually gives up, rolls down the window, and sticks her head out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't think I won't run your ass over.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah circles to the driver side window and bends down to be eye level with Mary. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">First you'd have to turn the engine on.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It is on you fucking idiot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, your battery is on. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Can we just talk outside? We can figure this out. Come on out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah tries the door, it's locked. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Stop that.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary presses the break and goes to push the car's start button. As she does, Dakotah reaches into the car and grabs her arm before she presses it, holding it firmly. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(very stern)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, you're wasted. Get out right now. I will go get your parents.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah keeps his hand on Mary's arm. She uses her other hand to try and pry it off.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(appalled)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now you're attacking me?  </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(screaming)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Get off!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah's demeanor changes, and he lets her arm go and backs out of the window. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, I'm going to get Richard.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah quickly heads back towards the house. As soon as he's out of the way, Mary, tears streaming down her eyes, puts the car into drive and begins peeling away.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah turns around and screams after her, and takes off following her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do not! Are you crazy?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She speeds down the driveway and turns into the street, erratically.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah runs the length of the driveway trying to catch up with her. He stops and looks out at the direction Mary drove away. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">NOVEMBER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. CHARLOTTE'S APARTMENT - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Charlotte are sitting on her couch, close to each other. Charlotte's apartment is a loft in the West Village, immaculate in decoration, with old furniture, lots of plants, and large windows.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The neighborhood is beautiful, I still don't know how you leave this for Brooklyn.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He leans back toward the end of the couch and sees a framed photo of Gustav Klimt's </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Portrait of Hermine Gallia.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You look just like her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte looks over to what Zev is referring to and breaks into a wide smile. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sarcastically)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My great-grandmother.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev does not pick up on the joke. She leans over and lies on him as they both look at the photo.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(perking up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What do you want to watch?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">You're</Text>
<Text Style=""> asking </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">me</Text>
<Text Style="">? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mmmm.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(she looks over at her closet)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let me see.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte stands up and walks over to her closet. She begins opening it then stops and turns to Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So tell me something. Did you really like those Rohmer movies or were you just trying to impress me?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(jokingly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, no, I just enjoy sitting for an hour and a half on the subway to see you. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You can be honest, I just want to know what you like!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm being honest! I really liked them! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She turns back to her closet and fully opens it, revealing shelves and shelves of DVDs. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pondering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay then... so you like European stuff... which you should, because they're the best... hmm...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">While Charlotte is scanning the shelves, Zev gets up, shocked, and walks to the closet.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Whoa, whoa, whoa, wait, what is this? You've got all of world cinema in this closet!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She turns to Zev and smiles.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You can be honest, is this a red flag?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, I love it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in awe)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This is passion.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(turning back to the shelves)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Anyways, maybe I should show you something Italian. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We did have pizza for dinner. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You need Fellini.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She takes </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">8½</Text>
<Text Style=""> out from the shelf.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's like the most famous of the Italians. Him and Antonioni, but </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">his</Text>
<Text Style=""> stuff is kinda slow. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Or...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking through the shelf and pulling out a DVD)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">Nights of Cabiria</Text>
<Text Style="">. It's one of his early ones, too.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How did you get all these? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've been collecting movies since middle school.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've been into film for that long? I'll be dead before I watch half of these.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T224005">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">yeah im not over the moon about this which is why i took my crack but im also not over the moon about mine in any way, but we can note it as an area to improve</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well, growing up I alway spent summers in the Hamptons, and I didn't have many friends back then. Not that I do now, but my only really close friend spent her summers in the south of France. So we wouldn't see each other until school started again. One year, we started watching the same movie on Monday, write a letter about what we thought, and by the end of the week, we'd send letters back. It made the summers less lonely.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">At twelve years old your preferred movies were black and white French New Waves about sexual </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(mispronouncing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">ennui?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Not quite. It started with everyday movies, then moved into Hollywood classics, and eventually my dad suggested we try some foreign films and it just grew from there.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a moment of silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Are you close with your dad?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Very. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Got it. Well this is really... something.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte smiles and brushes past him with the DVD in hand and heads to her DVD player, while Zev heads back to the couch.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So, does everyone who comes over get a tour of the closet?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, I don’t just have anybody over to watch Italian movies. Is that what you think of me?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm offended. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, no, no, it's not that! I'm sorry. Really. I'm just... here you are, with a movie closet in West Village... I'm in uncharted territory, that's all. I feel like a shmuck.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I like that about you. You're not like most guys I meet, trying to prove they know the world. And you're not a shmuck, you're just figuring things out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a pause.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What are most guys like? Dakotah?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte bends down and begins fiddling with the DVD player.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What is that supposed to mean?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Opportunistic, maybe? Hellbent on destruction?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ribbing him)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Are we a little jealous?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know... I mean, does he seem like somebody that really cares about art to you?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte, still bent over, turns her head to look at Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know. I think he cares about keeping the theater alive, and that should be the bottom line.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I get a weird vibe.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte stands up and starts walking back to the couch.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe he'll turn the place around and that way people will be able to enjoy the cinema for years to come, or discover it for the first time. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte sits back down on the couch, close to Zev, turns towards him, and begins running her fingers through his hair.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let's wait and see. He might turn the place around, you never know. And besides, let's not talk about work tonight. Let's just enjoy the movie. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte gives Zev one last quick kiss.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev kisses Charlotte on the head, then reaches over to switch off the lamp next to the couch while Charlotte clicks play on her remote.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The theater is unusually lively with pairs of teen boys waiting for the screening room to open for </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Midnight Cowboy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER BATHROOM - CONTINOUS </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert, Mary, Jimmy, Connie, and Zev are packed in closely in the bathroom. They are speaking in low voices.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary's arm is in a cast; she has a busted lip and a black eye.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If Jean Luc Retárd makes us run </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Mission Impossible, </Text>
<Text Style="">I'm going to burn this place to the ground.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quietly, shocked)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's pretty cute.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He doesn't look at all like Montgomery.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's going to turn us into a Regal. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shhh!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">FOOTSTEPS are heard approaching the bathroom. Robert turns the light off. The FOOTSTEPS subside. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte, I can't believe she set this whole thing up. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They were high school sweethearts.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev's heart sinks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I didn't know they knew each other.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy embraces Zev, who is confused by the gesture, busy being preoccupied by this new information.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A second later, the bathroom door swings open. Dakotah steps in and switches the light on.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">AHH!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah YELLS and jumps back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T225639">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">i can be on board with that</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jesus, you scared me!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(collecting himself)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Now, I don't want to overstep my boundaries but time theft costs corporations 57 million dollars a year, and we're out here fighting for pennies! We need to work together, this isn't me versus you, it's us keeping the theater alive. Can I count on you?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew are silent for a moment, looking to Mary, who gives Dakotah a stern, silent stare. They take this as a signal to hold their position against him and they file out of the bathroom. Mary is at the back of the group.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah puts his hand on Mary's shoulder to stop her as she attempts to pass him and leave the bathroom with the rest of the group.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(low voice)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm not going to say a word.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Should've just left me.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You could've really hurt yourself.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">At least I wouldn't have to bear what you're doing to the Four.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(frustrated, whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Can you get a grip?! You know better than all them, but you act like I'm a devil trying to shut you down.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You aren't?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(exasperated)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jesus.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary pushes past him, leaving Dakotah alone in the bathroom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew is filtering into the lobby from the bathroom. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy holds Zev back for a private chat.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, can I tell you something about trust?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(annoyed)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sure.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There was a point in my life when I did therapy twice a week, for $250 dollars an hour. That's $2,000 dollars a month, Zev. And you know what I did? I don't even know why, but sometimes I just couldn't stop myself.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know if I really want to hear this.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I lied. I was filthy liar. At first it was little things like "oh yeah, no I'm stuffed" when I had in fact not eaten at all. Then, one day, my therapist asked if I liked the Mets, because I was talking about living in Crown Heights. I've never watched a baseball game, I don't know the rules, but my mouth just said, "yeah, I've been a fan my whole life." </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pondering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe it's my subconscious wanting to really be from Brooklyn.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sternly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well it turned out that she'd watched them religiously since childhood with her father.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ironically)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh no.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I had to commit. I learned RBI's, Curveball, Umpire, Barry Bonds did steroids, a pitch killed a bird. I watched </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Bull Durham</Text>
<Text Style="">. I watched all the </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Seinfeld</Text>
<Text Style=""> episodes where George worked for the Yankees; the cotton uniforms! Every week I would have to look up the scores because all our sessions began to start with 5 minutes of baseball chat. For nine months I did that. Do you grasp the weight of that statement; how much money of the little money I earn that I've spent talking about the Mets?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I do. I really do.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(serious)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's a sickness, there has to be something seriously wrong with me. I'm 30 years old. I travel, on the subway, to an office, to sit across from a licensed psychotherapist, whose only job it is, is to accept me, unconditionally and without judgement. And I still can't do it Zev. I just can't. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(still annoyed)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's quite a story.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Anyways, what I'm trying to say is, a lie can be a lie, or it can be a truth untold... Do you understand what I'm trying to tell you? I wouldn't get involved unless I cared. We all do. You're our concessionaire.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stares at Jimmy for a moment, then glances at the stairs.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jimmy turns to walk away and Zev slips up the stairs to the projection booth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. PROJECTION BOOTH - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte is sitting in the projection booth when she hears a KNOCK on the door. She goes to open it, revealing Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(curt)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey. How's it going?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Good, good.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte is taking a DCP out of the projector.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(making small talk)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">So, </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Grease</Text>
<Text Style="">, huh?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, I don't think </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Pulp Fiction</Text>
<Text Style=""> fits into Nathan's grand plan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know, Dakotah was talking about his Dalton days earlier. That's where you went right? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Was he?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a touch aggressive)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You never told me you knew each other.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Why is that suddenly such a big deal? Do you want my whole resume? Mary went to Dalton too if you want the whole picture.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You weren't fucking Mary, or were you?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(hurt)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Why wouldn't you tell me? The other night, we were talking all about him...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Neither of us had a prom date but it wasn't anything romantic, we were kids. And when did my past become your business? Worry about the present. Who am I fucking now?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Me, but I'm not entirely sure I'm the only one.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't be a jerk! I thought he could help the theater, I spoke to Alan... and it's working! Does no one care about how there's actually people here tonight?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've been so defensive of the guy... what am I supposed to think?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(getting upset)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nothing! I've known men before you, I hate to break that headline. I'm allowed to have people from my past, friends or otherwise, that I still keep in touch with.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev starts to get worked up and becomes visibly angry.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're spending too many nights dancing in the theater 'til sunrise, lapping up every word they tell you. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Must be a Dalton thing, I wouldn't get it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(upset)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Why are you doing this to me? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm not doing anything to you. You lied to me!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I didn't lie!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(overlapping)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">By omission! A truth untold!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte begins to cry.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You go on and on about cinema, the art, and you let it all go to waste because you want to do a favor for some hotshot who doesn't know Antonini from... from </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Fast and Furious.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You don't have to be an asshole. That's just not true. This place was being run into the ground. Plus, I don't want to hear it. You wouldn't know who any of those people were if it weren't for me and--</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're right! And that's why I'm shocked! I thought of all people </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">you</Text>
<Text Style=""> would understand why what we do here is important. But hey, what's it to you? Place goes under, it's just another opportunity for daddy to come in with the bulldozers.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, what in the fuck are you talking about? Also don't bring my dad into this.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a tense pause.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(trying to defuse the situation)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe Dakotah'll save this place, he'll save it and more people will discover great film. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How? Where? One super villain movie at a time? Where's the art?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte is at a loss for words.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Look, I know you love him but the rest of us...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="Kenneth Geiler" DateTime="20210413T230710">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">just kidding</Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">Oh God, you asshole. Fuck you. You know what, I do have a history with him. We hooked up during summers in college, and I didn't want to tell you, because I thought those days were over. I thought we could just have something together, but now you're Sherlock Holmes'ing my past like I ever betrayed you? Honestly, get out of my booth and get out of my life.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev storms out. Charlotte is dumbstruck, unsure if she made the right decision turning the tables on Zev. She quickly pushes the thought away, locks the booth, and loads a reel for </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Midnight Cowboy</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As the film begins, she falls into her chair, tearing up.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - AFTERNOON</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The entire crew is gathered in the theater office, with Alan, Dakotah, and Nathan up at the front. Zev and Charlotte are seated on opposite ends of the room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(reading from a notebook)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">9% growth week over week for the last month. Concessions up 14%. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We are on pace for something really big, and it's only going to get better.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Going from four people to a dozen isn't really a breakthrough.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It has been starting to buzz a bit, I can't lie. Strangely it hasn't even been mostly teens, it's like dads who golf and Hell's Angels.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, I noticed this as well. I built an adjustment into my model and we're adding </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Magic Mike XXL </Text>
<Text Style="">to the slate.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary doesn't even flinch; she's numb to it now.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Growth is growth, and the best is yet to come. And I've noticed you all like to hang out after work, so to thank you, I'd like to treat the group to drinks tomorrow night at my place.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan is beaming.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Show some appreciation for Dakotah everyone. We're turning a new leaf!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE AND WARREN </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(deflated, under their breaths)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Elaine May.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER THAT NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The double header has finished and pairs of older biker men and middle aged white-collar dads file out of the theater; one pair flush red and holding hands, the others not as successful.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is behind the counter with Connie still perched near the ticket station, despite the lack of customers. Warren, Robert, and Jimmy are nowhere to be seen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie looks in Zev's direction. Zev replies with an exasperated expression. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Poor fellows. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(distraught)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They gave it a shot. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm not going to come to Mary's, I need a little extra rest tonight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Me too, actually. You take the G, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm headed in that direction, too.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CROSSFADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. BROOKLYN STREET - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Connie are walking together on the sidewalk.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know, growing up outside of New York, you don't really realize that people just exist here. You think of it as such an alien lifestyle.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What do you mean? I exist here. You're existing here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know, it's just different when you're on the outside looking in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They walk a few paces in silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I love walking on nights like tonight. When it's balmy, when the air takes on a sort of lightness, almost.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie smiles a little.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I guess that's what you meant by some of us just existing here. Brooklyn is Brooklyn, it's never been magical to me. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Where are you from, again? I'm sorry, I realized I totally forgot.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't think you ever asked. I'm from Memphis--well, Germantown, actually. It's a suburb.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(perking up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I love it, don't get me wrong, but it's definitely not enchanting.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(lighthearted)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Not many guys like me over there, I bet. I'd like to visit one day, if you ever go back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(she nods)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Definitely. I miss my family a lot. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(motioning to the stop)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Anyways, this is where you get on, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie and Zev arrive at the train stop. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, but you know what I could go for? An ice cream sandwich. They come in a two pack, if you're not one of those lactose people.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes! I don't know if you wanna walk this far, but the bodega across from my place has the Magnum Doves.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(considering, eyeing the subway)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't mind a stroll.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Are you sure? I don't want you to have to walk all the way back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's no problem! </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(trying to be clever)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I too love walking on nights like tonight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The pair begin walking down the street, away from the stop.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sorry if I'm dragging my feet, I go into my other job tomorrow and I hate it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(surprised)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Two jobs?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's at a little art studio in Long Island City. I was supposed to be working on craft books and pottery kits but it's proven to be way more corporate than artistic, which is the last thing I want to be involved with.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I had no idea you were into pottery.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Well... What I really want to do is be the person that comes up with the drawings for coloring books. For adults. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've never heard of someone coming to New York City to be an adult coloring book-ist.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I guess I just thought if I was gonna find my future, I was gonna find it here.</Text>
<Text Style="Bold"> </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A lot of people seem to think that, but take it from a local, I'm not so sure about all that.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I should really get back into coloring, it's been years probably. My colors always bled between the lines.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I just think people don't take time to appreciate the beauty of the world around them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie waves her hands, motioning to the quiet, empty street. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But when you're coloring, you're really focusing on it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And Cinema Four is sort of your halfway house to drawing full time?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I think so. I didn't really mean to get involved at the Four at all. One day I walked by and saw they were running a Studio Ghibli marathon. I came in, watched them all, and then Mary noticed me hanging around and asked if I wanted to apply.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How long do you think you can take tickets before you're all dried out?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It really depends. I think about it a lot. I don't think I could go back to Germantown. Maybe Memphis, Nashville... Or maybe somewhere totally different, like out west.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I never had that feeling growing up, that I had to go somewhere else. I could just take the G to Fulton and I was there. Everything is here, so why leave?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's why everyone comes here and pretends to be a local, right? It's the cliche. But I wouldn't trade growing up in Germantown for the world. I remember being a little girl, and being in my room late at night, on a Saturday night where I didn't have school the next day, and I'd hear a train way off in the distance. And that, and maybe the hum of a car way off, would be the only things I'd hear. And it would all seem, you know, the place where the train was, far off--it would all seem so mysterious and I'd wonder where the train was headed. And I'd feel so unbound and free. In New York, I know it sounds silly, but the train you hear is the subway, and you know exactly where it is and where it's going. There's no mystery, or at least not anymore. And I don't know if I wanna know everything all the time.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm sorry, I probably sound so stupid right now. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No... I understand you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie stops walking at her building, Zev keeps going a few paces before realizing. He looks back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(lightheartedly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Here she is.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But you know what I just remembered? I actually have some Talenti in my freezer. Any interest in just having that instead?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a pause.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay. Sure. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev walks behind Connie and follows her up the steps into her building.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A light flicks on on the third floor.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - THE FOLLOWING NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, Warren, Connie, Robert, and Zev are in the lobby hanging out. Dakotah, Charlotte and Nathan walk in from the screening room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to everyone)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You guys ready to head out? It's in Manhattan, which I know can seem treacherous.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(rudely)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We can't make it tonight, but any other time just let us know.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Rob and I are meeting with a big producer tonight, otherwise we'd love to...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, really?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev looks to the others and exchanges a look with Connie. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah walks over and wraps his arm around Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Four's company to me. We'll catch you all another night.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The four of them walk out of the theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. DAKOTAH'S APARTMENT - AN HOUR LATER </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte, Nathan, and Zev are in Dakotah's posh apartment living room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is in the kitchen getting drinks together. He walks into the living room with a tray of drinks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, I heard some great things about you. You've got good taste.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah winks at Zev suggestively.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(curt)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thank you. Charlotte, you don't live too far from here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, I do not.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah hands out drinks to the group.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">When you see Denis Lavant on screen and the way he moves his body, I mean it's pure magic. I'd take him over Peck or Dean or any of those guys.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(taking his drink)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Thanks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan sips his, expecting a mocktail given he does not drink. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He SHRIEKS.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Jesus fucking Christ!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He drops the glass and spills it all over his lap.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Charlotte are surprised. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan looks at the drink Charlotte is holding.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My Shirley Temple!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan, I'm so sorry, I must've mixed them up in the kitchen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan starts HEAVING. He runs to the bathroom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We're going to order up a Pedialyte!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll make you a new one.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Did I take the wrong drink? I didn't mean to.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(heading to the kitchen)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, no, that was on me.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah leaves the room. It's just Zev and Charlotte. It's silent for a few moments.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How have you been?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Why did you make me come?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The sound of a SHAKER can be heard in the back. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Look, I don't want to hurt you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Just leave me alone.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah comes back in with a new glass and sits across from them. Zev and Charlotte play nice while Dakotah is around.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Cheers! To good company, and better business. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They CLINK their glasses. Dakotah enjoys his sip immensely and then puts down his glass and brushes his legs. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(in a low voice)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'd like to tell you something Zev, if you promise to keep it between us. Only Nathan, Alan, Charlotte, and myself know. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte shoots Zev a look.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Dakotah)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't think you should. Nothing's official.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Relax. We're amongst friends. This is great news, Zev will be over the moon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(eyeing Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Whatever you feel comfortable with.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ever heard of the Paris theater? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've never been to Europe.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is momentarily confused.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(smiling slyly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Netflix, that's all I'll say.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's enough Dakotah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah downs his whisky and AAHs in delight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah... I've heard of it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">All I'm going to say is Hulu could be interested in premiering films in </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">their own</Text>
<Text Style=""> theater. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The Four? I love the place, but it's kind of a dump.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You'd be surprised what a paint job and new management does to a place.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah winks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah, enough.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've got a couple of suits coming to do a walk-though. It's supposed to be incognito, so play it cool. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shut it! He’ll tell all of them before dawn.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev wouldn't do that. We have a bond. Plus, nothing at the theater will change. Actually most corporate acquisitions leave the business exactly as is, save for a few operational efficiencies. The idea that corporate takeovers somehow kill the culture that existed is a falsehood. You would all get raises, benefits, there would be big premieres.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I wouldn't be surprised if they stage a lock in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(starting to slur his words)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If they botch this deal, they're going to have another thing coming. At least in the</Text>
<Text Style="Bold"> </Text>
<Text Style="">60s</Text>
<Text Style="Bold">, </Text>
<Text Style="">the hippies were against a war. The only thing Mary is against is crossing the East River. And for what? Because Manhattan is nice? Do kids in the South Sudan rest their heads on their pillows to dream of coming to America to live in a roach infested four bedroom in Ridgewood, Queens? No, God damn it! They dream about the Empire State Building, Central Park, brunch at Ladurée. This...this poor chic aesthetic, it's</Text>
<Text Style="Bold"> </Text>
<Text Style="">complete crap. If you were actually broke you'd be in Hoboken. And for some reason, everyone east of Williamsburg is an artist. When did being a regular person with a job become some sort of grand failure; a disgrace to humanity that we don't make paper-mache sculptures of our genitals?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(sheepishly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Actually, the male genitalia is vastly under represented in art. Mary is working on a photo series about it... It's called the Phallic Fallacy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The fallacy is that anyone gives a damn. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Did I do anything to offend them? They've been against the idea of me before I ever stepped foot into that lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Really, is what I'm trying to do so goddamn evil?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I-I don't think so. The theater's dying, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They hate the idea of someone like me actually helping them. Is it because of who my grandfather is? Where my family comes from? Would they rather I slum it in Flatbush and </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">pretend</Text>
<Text Style=""> I don’t have a trust fund? They'd start calling me Mary.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(stern)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah, relax.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They just want what's best for the Four.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do they really?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let me ask you something. You're a straight fellow</Text>
<Text Style="Bold">,</Text>
<Text Style=""> right? Do they look down on you for being a cis hetero, Plain Jane living life with no flavor?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No I haven't felt that at all. I actually invited them all over for dinner at my parents' in Bensonhurst. They seemed to enjoy that a lot, and it's no Brooklyn-chic or whatever you're saying.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(beginning to really slur his words)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ah, so they approved. You're a "real Brooklyn guy", that's a hall pass, congratulations. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You know what, I bet you think you got me figured out. Yeah, I'm rich and I'm handsome and I'm Montgomery Clift's grandson, but I'm no dickhead. You know where I was last night? While you were drinking Pabst and talking schmeers, I was in that very chair and I watched </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">8½</Text>
<Text Style=""> six times yesterday. And that's not even a record, ya dumb bitch. And let me tell ya another thing, Charlie Kauffman blows. Guy fuckin' sucks. We've all read books--well, some of us, maybe all those used bookstores in Bushwick are for show.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan is VOMITING in the bathroom down the hall. Dakotah turns back toward the bathroom.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(loudly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You okay, buddy?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Charlotte and Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On top of everything, he's a celiac.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN (O.S.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(slurring)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can't... I can't see...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Poor thing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah stands up, walks over to his sound system, and turns it up to drown out Nathan's hurls. MUSIC starts playing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm going to check on him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stands up and leaves the room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. DAKOTAH'S BATHROOM - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is standing over Nathan, who has his head halfway into the toilet bowl. Zev is patting his back.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm fine. Thank you my friend.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev empties a cup from the vanity and fills it with sink water.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Here, rinse.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan gurgles the water and spits it out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(taking a deep breath)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev slides to the door of the bathroom and peers into the living room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He sees Dakotah holding Charlotte's hand, rubbing it affectionally. Zev doesn't react. He returns to Nathan's side.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. CONNIE'S APARTMENT - LATER THAT NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev scans the buzzer list and then BUZZES 4C.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE (INTERCOM)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's me.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She BUZZES him in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. CONNIE'S APARTMENT - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie waits at the doorway, distraught. Zev climbs the stairwell and rushes into her apartment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev quickly takes off his coat and his shoes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(out of breath)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He's gonna sell the place. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Huh?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I was at Dakotah's, he told us.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're not making any sense!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is getting Hulu to buy the Four. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Whoa, what... what do they want with it?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I have no clue, but they're huge. It'll probably ruin everything.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, calm down. There's nothing we can do about it now. We'll tell the gang tomorrow and figure it out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I ran over here, I didn't know where to go. I had to tell you. Charlotte knows, and they all know.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev looks up at Connie, clearly distraught.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's okay.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't think I've ever felt this way about someone. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They embrace. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quiet)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I love you. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie leads Zev over to the couch and sits him down.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Try to relax.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie goes to her fridge and brings Zev a beer. He takes a big swig.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(defeated)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What a fucking night. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I know I'm probably overreacting. It's just, I...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can't paint, I can't play an instrument, I...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(starting to tear up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I've never had any outlet for expression and I finally found something that made it feel like I was doing something other than just existing. And now it's going away.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie takes a seat next to Zev. He wipes away his tears as she turns on the TV and scrolls through various streaming options, skipping over Hulu. </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Ace Ventura: When Nature Calls </Text>
<Text Style="">beings to play.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie scoots closer into Zev and he embraces her. They break into smiles at Jim Carrey's whimsical performance.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TELEVISION (O.S.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do not fret, my little woodland friend, for your life is in the hands of Ace Ventura... pet detective.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold">TITLE CARD: </Text>
<Text Style="AllCaps+Bold+Underline">DECEMBER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - AFTERNOON </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Afternoon sun bathes the theater lobby, which seems atypically lively. It's a Saturday, so the full staff is working. Connie is in the ticketing position and Zev is behind the counter. The front doors swing open and Dakotah walks in with two men dressed in suits tailing him.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew take instant notice of the SUITED MEN and exchange tense glances.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH (O.S)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the suited men)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She was built in '32--the Golden Era of theater construction. I'm sure you're well aware of where this place stands in cinema history. They premiered </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Break</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">fast at Tiffany's, </Text>
<Text Style="">it was the local haunt for all the big names back then</Text>
<Text Style="Italic">.</Text>
<Text Style="Italic"> </Text>
<Text Style="">Obviously, now we're in a bit of a slump, but with a little help...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary and Jimmy look at Zev. Zev nods.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah approaches the concession stand with the suits.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the suits)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Can we get you something? Zev here is the best in the business.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(polite)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We're alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #2</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Dakotah)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Tuesday though, can you make sure you have the melted cheese machine up and running</Text>
<Text Style="Bold">? </Text>
<Text Style="">I can't sit through a 'flick without it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I know what you mean. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah gives Zev a look.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text></Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sure thing. What's on Tuesday?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">These gentlemen here are going to help us do a little test run. And if things are in working order, eventually a premiere.  </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(jokingly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We have to make sure that projector up there still runs.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">On that note, let's head up to the booth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah points to the stairs leading up the balcony and motions to the suits to head that way. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll meet you guys right over there in just a minute. I just have a question to ask Zev here. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The suits walk off, leaving Dakotah and Zev alone.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zevvy, buddy, I'm sorry. Sometimes I hit the hooch a little too hard and go off the rails a bit. But you heard what I said, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, Charlie Kauffman blows.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Be that as it may, I'm talking about all the other stuff. Now again, let's keep what's going on between us, but I wanted you to be in the know. You're a smart kid, you get it. We're cool, right?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, we're cool.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alright.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah nods to Zev, then turns to meet the suits at the bottom of the stairs. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the suits)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sorry about that gentleman. Anyways, Charlotte'll give you the rundown... she's really what keeps this place running.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah leads the suits up the stairs to the balcony. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CROSSFADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew sit together in the lobby somberly, drinking wine. Zev sits close to Connie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Zev)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What exactly did he say the other night?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a bit flustered)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He asked me if I had ever been to some Parisian theater and talked about Netflix... I had no idea they were showing up so soon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And at the stand?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah said Tuesday they're running a test premiere, then they went to talk to Charlotte.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, who had has been staring off at the theater walls, not very engaged in the conversation, speaks aloud, not directly to the group, just to herself, loud enough for the group to hear.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">If any one of you comes to watch a movie here after the takeover, I'm going to punch you in the liver until you die.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Are you nuts, we would never.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Then you're worry-free.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe now I'll have time to focus on my poetry.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You've worked here for eight years, your job mainly consists of walking past this lobby every three hours, watching movies whenever you want, and handing us an envelope with our money twice a month. Do you really think that's what been holding you back from your poetry career?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary, be nice! He's being optimistic.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, she's right. I'll be job hunting anyway. I interned at the public library when I just moved to the city, maybe they need a general manager.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary the murderer and Jimmy the balding library cop. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the group)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This is </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">our</Text>
<Text Style=""> theater. You're not even going to try and stop him?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What're you gunna do? Chain yourself to the screening room?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I don't know! Sabotage the deal, send Dakotah packing back to Dartmouth.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, okay Danny Ocean. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, why not?! Ask yourself what we have at our disposal. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group stares at Zev in silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Art! The single most powerful tool against a profit-driven, megalomanic society.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew stares on, taken aback by his zeal.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let's show them what artists are made of. Robert and Warren, they've been making movies for ages now.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Correction, they've been </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">talking </Text>
<Text Style="">about </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">a </Text>
<Text Style="">movie for ages now.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh shut up, Secret Dante.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte showed me how to use the projector, I can get her out of the booth and put on our own movie. We'll show those suits what they're destroying.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll help.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Warren and I can provide the equipment and aesthetic sensibilities. Dante?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Fuck it, it's not gonna make a difference but might as well go out with a bang.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew looks to Mary, who is the only uncommitted member. She looks at Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sure, I'll join this revolution...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary fishes a platinum American Express out of her pocket and holds it up to the crew.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE AND WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robin Hood!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO BLACK.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It is after closing hours at the theater. The lobby is still as Alan, Dakotah, Nathan, and a dozen SUITED MEN, two of them the same men from the day before, exit Alan's office.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew is shooting nervous glances at each other as they watch the business people waltz through the lobby.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(excited)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, really, thank you for coming, it means a lot. I have to run home to feed the cats, but let's talk tomorrow, and Dakotah and I will sync. And then hopefully we get the lawyers to fill in the dotted lines.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The business men shake Alan's hand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #2</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A pleasure. Thanks for having us.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan touches their shoulders warmly. He exits the theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Nathan)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Go get these gentlemen some nachos and...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the business men)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Drinks? We've got the hard stuff if you're interested.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Just a round of Sprites.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Nathan nods and heads to the concession stand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hello, Zev. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey, Nate. How are you feeling? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Quite alright now. Did you see the executives?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah ushers the business men into the screening room as the crew watch them pensively.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yes, I did. What are they screening?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We're not allow to talk about it... Nachos, please.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev turns around to prepare the nachos when Robert comes behind into the concession stand area. He has a messenger bag over his shoulder.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(acting pleasant)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ahoy, Nathanial.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert. Did you see the executives?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sure did.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert bends down to "grab a snack" and leaves the messenger bag down there.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll catch you guys later.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He leaves.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(with the nachos)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay... nachos. Anything else?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">NATHAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sprites for everyone.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev nods and turns to the soda machine as Jimmy comes into the concession stand. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JIMMY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll finish these out and bring everything in. Can you make sure the cubby area is tidied up with Connie? We need to be showing our best.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sure thing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He ducks down and subtly grabs the messenger bag. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He feigns toward the cubby area, and as Nathan is distracted holding Sprites and nachos, Zev slinks up the stairs toward the balcony.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, shrouded in darkness, is quietly in the balcony area, out of view of the projection window. He is nervous. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He peers down at the orchestra to see the business men and Dakotah all seated and Nathan entering the room with their snacks.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah is sitting between the two suits as suit #1 takes in his environment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This place really is beautiful. What'a fuckin' gem you found us.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #2</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Dakotah)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Imagine this place packed - the balcony. Standing room only. This happened because of you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #1</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(turning to Dakotah)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're an extremely impressive young man. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The suit shakes Dakotah's hand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah receives it proudly like a cadet from his general.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The group sits back, staring forward at the screen, as the movie should be starting.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Without looking away from the screen, Suit #2 subtly passes an envelope into Dakotah's jacket pocket, at which point he turns to Dakotah.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #2</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(winking)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Finder's fee.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah feels the touch of the envelope on his chest and it feels like the reception of a purple heart.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev knocks on the projection room door. The bag is to the side, out of Charlotte's sight.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Char.... Charlotte. We need you.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte opens the door a crack.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(whispering)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Leave me alone!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(frantic)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wait -</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(holding the door from being closed on him)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah sent me up here. He - he asked me - the executives asked him - he needs to know... </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(unsure)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">How many cans of film do we have left? I can't remember it was something technical. He said run up and ask you and I messed up and I don't remember.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(mad)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Wait. What? That doesn't make any sense.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(nervous)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I can't remember! He needs to know now. They want it before the movie starts.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're really something...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte hastily exits.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Okay...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After holding the door open for Charlotte, Zev slips into the projection booth. He locks the door, surveys the booth, drops Robert's bag, and begins fishing through it. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte is speed walking up the aisle to Dakotah's row. Dakotah is surprised to see her.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What are you doing? We should be starting now!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHARLOTTE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev said - </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The projector starts up, Dakotah and Charlotte peer up. The business people have no idea something has gone astray.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">After a countdown reel, an image forms on the silver screen:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Mary Von Erb Presents"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"A Film By Robert O'Brien Love"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Shot by Warren Gilles"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Written by James S. Smith"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Art Direction by Concetta 'Connie' Wong"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The sound of popcorn POPPING plays over a black screen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - NIGHT - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The film fades into an image of the Cinema Four lobby, with Warren, Mary, Jimmy, and Connie all scattered in different parts of the lobby, staring directly at the camera. The camera pans forward, the scattered crew turning their heads to keep their eyes locked on the camera as it passes. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The POPPING morphs into a more ominous sound as the camera reaches the bottom of the stairs leading to the projection booth. The camera begins mounting the stairs, clearly carried by hand. No time to stabilize in post. The image fades. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - MOMENTS LATER - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev walks through the door leading to the balcony, and begins walking slowly down the balcony aisle steps.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They say films are our collective memory, our subconscious, if you will. Then what about the movie palace? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev reaches the railing of the balcony and looks down. He puts his hands on the railing, grips them tight, then begins to lunge himself off.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. NEW YORK STREETS - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Archival images of old movie palaces being imploded play. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What happens when a culture destroys its very own subconscious? We may soon find out. Gibbon theorized about how empires die. A glib corporation will show us how a culture dies.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, BALCONY - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is hanging from the theater balcony, his legs flailing. He SCREAMS. A close up of his face shows perspiration and extreme anguish.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The last gasps of a way of life.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The camera pans from Zev's face to the expanse below, where Warren, Mary, Jimmy, and Connie are standing, pointing and laughing inaudibly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">While the so-called shakers and movers laugh.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert, dressed in a cheap suit and smoking a cigar, sits in Alan's office chair. He LAUGHS and stands up, puffing smoke, as Mary, dressed in a satin blouse and a long khaki skirt walks into the frame.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - MOMENTS LATER - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary is reclining on the office desk as Robert begins untying her blouse, the room now filled with smoke. He continues laughing. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The rot of industry. Has it always been a cancer? Has it always leached upon cinema? Why, we must ask, did we build the palaces in the first place?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - LATER - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Robert is now supine on the desk, Zev standing over him, reigning blows upon him with a film reel. Robert cowers and attempts to use his arms to protect his face.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But the little guy will always stand tall. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATER - ON SCREEN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Again we see Warren, Mary, Jimmy, and Connie standing still, staring at the camera.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN, MARY, JIMMY, AND CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Whose side will you be on?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - CONTINUOUS</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The house lights raise slightly, the room is dim but horrified faces are visible.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The executives look at Dakotah with indifference; they'll find another theater to buy. They get up silently and file out to the aisle, and out of the screening room. Two of the executives carry a third who's passed out in shock.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SUIT #4</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Dakotah)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He always passes out when he watches something that sucks, but it hasn't been this bad since</Text>
<Text Style="Italic"> Anomalisa</Text>
<Text Style="">. Expect a medical bill.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">In the very back rows of the theater, Robert, Jimmy, Warren, Connie, and Mary sit victoriously. They are all clapping and hollering in celebration. Robert leans back in his chair, having finally seen one of his films on the big screen.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah enters a rage and Charlotte sobs, in shock at what has just happened. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What the hell is wrong with you people?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(walking out of the row)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This is insanity. This is pure evil. You worthless degenerates! You hipster scum fucks, you have no respect for anything in this world.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah rips the envelope to shreds and storms out of the theater.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I was going to save this dump!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte runs out chasing him, in tears.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Dakotah stomps back into the theater and looks at the crew.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DAKOTAH</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And Mary, your Mother Theresa, you know where she'll spend this weekend while you all file for unemployment? In Southampton, drinking a glass of claret with the so-called</Text>
<Text Style="Italic"> shakers and movers</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Mary's face is flush red with embarrassment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev stands in the projection booth, blank faced.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - NEXT MORNING</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Following a night of raucous fun by the crew, the screening room is in disarray. Empty bottles of alcohol, snacks, confetti, and kazoos cover the floors and chairs. The only light comes from the projector, which was left running with nothing to play.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew is scattered across the orchestra seats, passed out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">At the far end of the theater, a crevice of light forms as the entrance is opened. Alan walks in.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Silently, emotionless, he scans the room and absorbs the scene. Then he turns and exits, back into the corridor and out of the screening room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The SLAM of the screening room door awakens Zev, with Connie unperturbed, still leaning up against him in slumber. In a groggy state he too scans the wreckage of last night's celebration. He softly moves Connie's head from his chest to the back of the chair and slinks into the aisle. He saunters to the screening room exit.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev peeks his head out of the screening room door to find Alan slowly walking through the lobby, looking around at the walls and displayed artifacts.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is careful to stay unnoticed, unsettled by Alan's reaction, or rather non-reaction. Alan's back is to the screening room door, as he looks at the posters lining the wall.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're going to need a new job.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, having expected anger, comes fully out of the door. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Me, sir?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan, still talking away from Zev, starts walking to his office.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(fatherly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Come, let's see who I can call. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is confused, but gingerly walks after Alan to his office.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER OFFICE - MOMENTS LATER</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan is at his desk when Zev walks through the door. Seeing his face clearly for the first time in the light, it is evident that Alan has had a rough night. His face is sunken, eyes dried out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan motions for him to take a seat. Zev sits timidly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you like salad, Zev?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, nervous and confused, does not compute the question. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you like salad. Be honest, do you like your greens?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Not really, no... I'd rather have a burger.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan sighs deeply.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Me too, kid. Unfortunately, Silver Screen Salads only serves one thing. They offered me a 10% stake if I didn't renew the lease. You're not offended if I don't feel inclined to recommend you and your friends to new management?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev thinks Alan's completely lost his mind.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Are you okay?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a long silence.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do you think I do this for the money?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I started working concessions here in '76, in high school. Then I was the projectionist, and  then the manager, which paid my way through college. After college, I left to work in sales. A few years later this place was basically a dump. Duncan, the owner, passed away in '88, and on the day of his funeral I stopped at TD Bank and took a loan against my apartment for $30 thousand dollars. His kids wanted nothing to do with the place, I probably could've gotten it for half that. It's been 33 years. I gave her my heart and soul and the lights never went out. They've been dim, but never out.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan, proud, triumphant, pauses.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">What do you want to do with your life, Zev? </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">This is... was... I enjoyed working here. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan throws his arms up in purposefully satirical protest.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You poured melted butter!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(quick retort)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah, but it was fun! Jimmy and Mary, they all took me in; I found out about Godard, Antonioni, Coppola. I never knew movies were art. It's cooler than anything. I feel it just sitting here.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev sits back in his chair, a look of exasperation on his face. Alan notices Zev's realization.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(playfully)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Charlotte ever run </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">The Last Picture Show </Text>
<Text Style="">for you? She loves that movie.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev looks at Alan, confused.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, she didn't.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">That's a damn shame. You'll never get to see Cybil Shepard, 64 feet wide, with your back pressed up against the velvet with an ice cold Coke, absolutely tented. Not in Bensonhurst.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan pauses.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Take it from a fellow Brooklyn kid: when you're young, you can go around being content that you’re smarter than everyone. When you get a little older, you’ve gotta prove it.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan leans back in his chair, looks up to the ceiling in thought.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe I would've done it too. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">But probably not. Charlotte told me the movie sucked...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(a pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Maybe that was the point, they walked.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(perking up)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She did say the acting wasn't half bad. Then again, maybe Charlotte still has a soft spot for you. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Do yourself a favor, do something with your life besides complain about what you don't have. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(pause)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Except a job, you're going to need one of those. Your world can be bigger than butter.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He gets up, and on his way out of the office pats Zev on his shoulder goodbye. Not lovingly, but decisive. Zev stays in his chair, looking lost.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S BEDROOM - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is lying on his back, in bed, above the covers. All the lights are off and the curtain is drawn; the only light source is his fish tank. His eyes are wide open. He looks lost in thought.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S APARTMENT, LIVING ROOM - AFTERNOON - DAYDREAM</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev's apartment is on a high floor of a glass building in Long Island City, overlooking Manhattan.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo and Sheryl sit closely on his couch, dressed up in their Saturday best. Their eyes light up as Zev, in a tuxedo, enters the room. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Shlomo springs up and embraces Zev with a hug.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHLOMO</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(so proud)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My boy. My boy. Shalom malom kitsuanu. Hashem leads you to the promised land!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Sheryl dabs her teary eyes.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The car's here, we need to go.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">She rushes toward the door, stopping to check herself out in the mirror. As Shlomo passes, she turns to tuck his shirt further into his pants.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You had to wear this shirt?!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(from the hallway)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let's go!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. ZEV'S BUILDING - MOMENTS LATER - DAYDREAM</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, Sheryl, and Shlomo walk out of the lobby doors to the sidewalk.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie, window rolled down, smiles at Zev from the the back seat of a luxury Lincoln town car. She throws open the door and Zev and Sheryl get in the back, while Shlomo sits in the front passenger seat.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SHERYL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Connie, kissing her on the cheek)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Don't you look wonderful, Sweetie!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The car drives off.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. THEATER LOBBY - LATE AFTERNOON - DAYDREAM</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The lobby is lit beautifully, the dying light of the summer afternoon pouring in. Alan paces around in the lobby, checking his watch.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Through the glass doors of the theater, he sees the Lincoln pull up to the curb. He rushes to the doors to meet them.   </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As Alan holds the door open, he ignores the four of them in order to berate the LIMO DRIVER.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">45 minutes late, you worthless son of a bitch!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan quickly forgets his anger and turns to embrace Zev lovingly.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm so proud of you, Zev.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I wouldn't have wanted it to happen anywhere else.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">It's packed.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(giddy, low voice)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I think I saw Rex Reed in the fourth row.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Rex Reed?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Only </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">the</Text>
<Text Style=""> biggest name in film criticism.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alan turns his attention to Connie, Shlomo, and Sheryl, who are a feet few behind them.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ALAN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Connie)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie, dear, you look ravishing. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to the Sterns)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And you must be Mr. and Mrs. Stern How proud you must be.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(ushering them warmly)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Let's head in to the theater... give the kid a moment.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Smiling, the four of them head to the theater. Zev, meanwhile, walks over to where the rest of the crew is gathered. Mary goes in for a hug.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">My little artiste! Lay it on me! You know you still have to pick up some shifts every now and again.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(interrupting)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Were those your parents over there?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WARREN</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Cute. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'll introduce you after the show. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ROBERT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Have you seen the theater yet?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No, I haven't. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MARY</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Oh you gotta go see it. The General got it all set up for you--it looks gorgeous.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The crew walks away and Zev begins to walk towards the screening room. On his way, he happens to glance up the stairs leading to the projection booth, where he sees Charlotte sitting, looking down, smiling. He smiles back and she winks. They look at each other for a minute, and then Zev continues on.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - LATER - DAYDREAM</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The screening room is filled to the brim with well-dressed PATRONS. The General is in the back, broom and pale in hand.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev enters, and The General places a warm hand on his shoulder.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">THE GENERAL</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(completely coherent)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">We're proud of you. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(looking out at the crowd)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Stay calm. You already did the hard work. Now just sit back, relax, and enjoy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev looks down with a smile as The General nudges him forward.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev emerges into the audience's view. They immediately give him a standing ovation. Zev receives the praise with humility. He waves and takes a small bow as walks up the aisle to the row he sat in when he first watched </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Breathless</Text>
<Text Style="">.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He takes his seat next to Connie, followed by his mother and father, Alan, Mary, Jimmy, Robert, and Warren. The lights go down alongside the clapping as the film starts. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A series of title cards are presented on screen:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"With grant funding from the </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Brooklyn Historical Society"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Dedicated to: </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">the memory of a time and a place</Text>
<Text Style="">"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"The Family Turst of Mary Von Erb Productions Presents"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Directed by Robert O. Love"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Based on an original screenplay by Warren Gilles"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">"Zev Stern in"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="Italic">"Cinema Five</Text>
<Text Style="">"</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. SCREENING ROOM, ORCHESTRA - TWO HOURS LATER - DAYDREAM</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">As the movie reaches its conclusion, all of the audience is crying.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (V.O.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">And that's what this theater is about. Not PROFIT, but ART.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Music wells up and the credits begin to play. The audience jumps up to cheer. Connie pounces on Zev with a big hug, and his mom pushes her out of the way so she can get a kiss in while wiping away a tear. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The pandemonium between Zev and his family calms down but the audience continues to clap. Connie looks him in the eyes then squeezes his hand. Zev looks forward in awe of the enthusiastic reaction. Connie pulls on his arm a little so he'll bring his ear down to her level. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">You're gonna be rich!</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, looking a little taken aback, nods and gets a big grin on his face. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S BEDROOM - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev, now sideways, is smiling when he snaps out of his day dream. He adjusts himself back to reality. He sits up in his bed and after a few moments of thought, he reaches over and grabs his phone. He makes a call. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Hey it's me. Are you up yet?</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A brief silence. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Yeah. Anyway, I'll be over at Mary's in a bit, I'll pick you up.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A pause. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">No I'm not coming up, you're coming down! I hate when we show up an hour after everyone else - it's embarrassing.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">A pause.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Alright, see you soon.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev hangs up, gets out of bed, throws on his clothes, and fixes his hair in the mirror.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(Italian style)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Ayyy.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">He walks out of his room.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There is a newly taped-on </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">Saturday Night Fever </Text>
<Text Style="">poster on the wall.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ZEV (O.S.)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(to Sheryl)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I'm taking the car. I might be late. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">(Brooklyn Italian Accent)</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Relax Ma, we're just goin' dancin'...</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The front door opens and closes. </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">The ENGINE of Zev's car rumbles and ultimately fades into the distance as he drives away from the house.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">INT. ZEV'S CAR - NIGHT</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev is driving with Connie in the car.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">They pass the location of Cinema Four and see construction workers with "Ladue Construction" vests. They have a group just set up the new marquee - "Silver Screen Salads". </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">There's a group protesting the building. One man stands on a crate with a megaphone. Zev and Connie HEAR him yelling "Cinema Four is a landmark in history, it must be saved." </Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Connie hangs her head out of the window as they pass.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Character" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CONNIE</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Dialogue" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">I wonder if they're hiring.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Action" Alignment="Left">
<Text Style="">Zev and Connie laugh, she rests his head on his shoulder as they drive. Cinema Salads in the rear view until it disappears into the distance.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Type="Transition" Alignment="Right">
<Text Style="AllCaps"> FADE TO BLACK.</Text>

				<UserParagraphData>
					
				</UserParagraphData>
			</Paragraph>

      </Content>
      
